107  : isolate_(isolate),
108  local_isolate_(isolate_->main_thread_local_isolate()),
109  code_desc_(desc),
110  kind_(kind) {}

112 Factory::CodeBuilder::CodeBuilder(LocalIsolate* local_isolate,
113  const CodeDesc& desc, CodeKind kind)
114  : isolate_(local_isolate->GetMainThreadIsolateUnsafe()),
115  local_isolate_(local_isolate),
116  code_desc_(desc),
117  kind_(kind) {}

124 Handle<Code> Factory::CodeBuilder::NewCode(const NewCodeOptions& options) {

127 
128 MaybeHandle<Code> Factory::CodeBuilder::BuildInternal(
129  bool retry_allocation_or_fail) {
130  DirectHandle<TrustedByteArray> reloc_info =
131  NewTrustedByteArray(code_desc_.reloc_size);
132 
133  // Basic block profiling data for builtins is stored in the JS heap rather
134  // than in separately-allocated C++ objects. Allocate that data now if
135  // appropriate.
136  DirectHandle<OnHeapBasicBlockProfilerData> on_heap_profiler_data;
137  if (V8_UNLIKELY(profiler_data_ && isolate_->IsGeneratingEmbeddedBuiltins())) {
138  on_heap_profiler_data = profiler_data_->CopyToJSHeap(isolate_);
139 
140  // Add the on-heap data to a global list, which keeps it alive and allows
141  // iteration.
142  DirectHandle<ArrayList> list(isolate_->heap()->basic_block_profiling_data(),
143  isolate_);
144  DirectHandle<ArrayList> new_list = ArrayList::Add(
145  isolate_, list, on_heap_profiler_data, AllocationType::kOld);
146  isolate_->heap()->SetBasicBlockProfilingData(new_list);
147  }
148 
149  Tagged<HeapObject> istream_allocation =
150  AllocateUninitializedInstructionStream(retry_allocation_or_fail);
151  if (istream_allocation.is_null()) {
152  return {};
153  }
154 
155  Handle<InstructionStream> istream;
156  {
157  // The InstructionStream object has not been fully initialized yet. We
158  // rely on the fact that no allocation will happen from this point on.
159  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
160  Tagged<InstructionStream> raw_istream = InstructionStream::Initialize(
161  istream_allocation,
162  ReadOnlyRoots(local_isolate_).instruction_stream_map(),
163  code_desc_.body_size(), code_desc_.constant_pool_offset, *reloc_info);
164  istream = handle(raw_istream, local_isolate_);
165  DCHECK(IsAligned(istream->instruction_start(), kCodeAlignment));
166  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!local_isolate_->heap()->heap()->code_region().is_empty(),
167  local_isolate_->heap()->heap()->code_region().contains(
168  istream->address()));
169  }
170 
171  Handle<Code> code;
172  {
173  static_assert(InstructionStream::kOnHeapBodyIsContiguous);
174 
175  NewCodeOptions new_code_options = {
176  kind_,
177  builtin_,
178  is_context_specialized_,
179  is_turbofanned_,
180  parameter_count_,
181  code_desc_.instruction_size(),
182  code_desc_.metadata_size(),
183  inlined_bytecode_size_,
184  osr_offset_,
185  code_desc_.handler_table_offset_relative(),
186  code_desc_.constant_pool_offset_relative(),
187  code_desc_.code_comments_offset_relative(),
188  code_desc_.jump_table_info_offset_relative(),
189  code_desc_.unwinding_info_offset_relative(),
190  interpreter_data_,
191  deoptimization_data_,
192  bytecode_offset_table_,
193  source_position_table_,
194  istream,
195  /*instruction_start=*/kNullAddress,
196  };
197  code = NewCode(new_code_options);
198  DCHECK_EQ(istream->body_size(), code->body_size());
199 
200  {
201  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
202  Tagged<InstructionStream> raw_istream = *istream;
203 
204  // Allow self references to created code object by patching the handle to
205  // point to the newly allocated InstructionStream object.
206  Handle<Object> self_reference;
207  if (self_reference_.ToHandle(&self_reference)) {
208  DCHECK_EQ(*self_reference,
209  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate_).self_reference_marker());
210  DCHECK_NE(kind_, CodeKind::BASELINE);
211  if (isolate_->IsGeneratingEmbeddedBuiltins()) {
212  isolate_->builtins_constants_table_builder()->PatchSelfReference(
213  self_reference, istream);
214  }
215  self_reference.PatchValue(raw_istream);
216  }
217 
218  // Likewise, any references to the basic block counters marker need to be
219  // updated to point to the newly-allocated counters array.
220  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!on_heap_profiler_data.is_null())) {
221  isolate_->builtins_constants_table_builder()
222  ->PatchBasicBlockCountersReference(
223  handle(on_heap_profiler_data->counts(), isolate_));
224  }
225 
226  // Migrate generated code.
227  // The generated code can contain embedded objects (typically from
228  // handles) in a pointer-to-tagged-value format (i.e. with indirection
229  // like a handle) that are dereferenced during the copy to point
230  // directly to the actual heap objects. These pointers can include
231  // references to the code object itself, through the self_reference
232  // parameter.
233  istream->Finalize(*code, *reloc_info, code_desc_, isolate_->heap());
234 
235 #ifdef VERIFY_HEAP
236  if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
237  HeapObject::VerifyCodePointer(isolate_, raw_istream);
238  }
239 #endif
240  }
241  }
242 
243  // TODO(leszeks): Remove stack_slots_, it's already in the instruction stream.
244  DCHECK_EQ(stack_slots_, code->stack_slots());
245 
246 #ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
247  if (V8_UNLIKELY(profiler_data_ && v8_flags.turbo_profiling_verbose)) {
248  std::ostringstream os;
249  code->Disassemble(nullptr, os, isolate_);
250  if (!on_heap_profiler_data.is_null()) {
251  DirectHandle<String> disassembly =
252  local_isolate_->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
253  os.str().c_str(), AllocationType::kOld);
254  on_heap_profiler_data->set_code(*disassembly);
255  } else {
256  profiler_data_->SetCode(os);
257  }
258  }
259 #endif // ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
260 
261  return code;
262 }
263 
264 Tagged<HeapObject> Factory::CodeBuilder::AllocateUninitializedInstructionStream(
265  bool retry_allocation_or_fail) {
266  LocalHeap* heap = local_isolate_->heap();
267  Tagged<HeapObject> result;
268  const int object_size = InstructionStream::SizeFor(code_desc_.body_size());
269  if (retry_allocation_or_fail) {
270  // Only allowed to do `retry_allocation_or_fail` from the main thread.
271  // TODO(leszeks): Remove the retrying allocation, always use TryBuild in
272  // the code builder.
273  DCHECK(local_isolate_->is_main_thread());
274  result =
275  heap->heap()->allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(
276  object_size, AllocationType::kCode, AllocationOrigin::kRuntime);
277  CHECK(!result.is_null());
278  return result;
279  } else {
280  // Return null if we cannot allocate the code object.
281  return heap->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kLightRetry>(
282  object_size, AllocationType::kCode);
283  }
284 }
285 
286 MaybeHandle<Code> Factory::CodeBuilder::TryBuild() {
287  return BuildInternal(false);
288 }
289 
290 Handle<Code> Factory::CodeBuilder::Build() {
291  return BuildInternal(true).ToHandleChecked();
292 }

294 Tagged<HeapObject> Factory::AllocateRaw(int size, AllocationType allocation,
295  AllocationAlignment alignment,
296  AllocationHint hint) {
297  return allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(
298  size, allocation, AllocationOrigin::kRuntime, alignment, hint);
299 }
300 
301 Tagged<HeapObject> Factory::AllocateRawWithAllocationSite(
302  DirectHandle<Map> map, AllocationType allocation,
303  DirectHandle<AllocationSite> allocation_site) {
304  DCHECK_NE(map->instance_type(), MAP_TYPE);
305  const auto [write_barrier_mode, should_allocate_memento] =
306  allocation == AllocationType::kYoung
307  ? std::pair{SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER, !allocation_site.is_null()}
308  : std::pair{UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER, false};
309  DCHECK_IMPLIES(should_allocate_memento, V8_ALLOCATION_SITE_TRACKING_BOOL);
310  const int instance_size = map->instance_size();
311  const int allocation_size =
312  should_allocate_memento
313  ? instance_size +
314  ALIGN_TO_ALLOCATION_ALIGNMENT(sizeof(AllocationMemento))
315  : instance_size;
316  Tagged<HeapObject> result =
317  allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(allocation_size,
318  allocation);
319  result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map, write_barrier_mode);
320  if (should_allocate_memento) {
321  const int aligned_size = ALIGN_TO_ALLOCATION_ALIGNMENT(instance_size);
322  Tagged<AllocationMemento> alloc_memento = UncheckedCast<AllocationMemento>(
323  Tagged<Object>(result.ptr() + aligned_size));
324  InitializeAllocationMemento(alloc_memento, *allocation_site);
325  }
326  return result;
327 }
328 
329 void Factory::InitializeAllocationMemento(
330  Tagged<AllocationMemento> memento, Tagged<AllocationSite> allocation_site) {
331  DCHECK(V8_ALLOCATION_SITE_TRACKING_BOOL);
332  memento->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *allocation_memento_map(),
333  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
334  memento->set_allocation_site(allocation_site, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
335  if (v8_flags.allocation_site_pretenuring) {
336  allocation_site->IncrementMementoCreateCount();
337  }
338 }
339 
340 Tagged<HeapObject> Factory::New(DirectHandle<Map> map,
341  AllocationType allocation) {
342  DCHECK(map->instance_type() != MAP_TYPE);
343  int size = map->instance_size();
344  Tagged<HeapObject> result =
345  allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(size,
346  allocation);
347  // New space objects are allocated white.
348  WriteBarrierMode write_barrier_mode = allocation == AllocationType::kYoung
349  ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER
350  : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
351  result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map, write_barrier_mode);
352  return result;
353 }
354 
355 DirectHandle<HeapObject> Factory::NewFillerObject(int size,
356  AllocationAlignment alignment,
357  AllocationType allocation,
358  AllocationOrigin origin) {
359  Heap* heap = isolate()->heap();
360  Tagged<HeapObject> result =
361  allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(
362  size, allocation, origin, alignment);
363  heap->CreateFillerObjectAt(result.address(), size);
364  return DirectHandle<HeapObject>(result, isolate());
365 }

367 DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> Factory::NewPrototypeInfo() {
368  auto result = NewStructInternal<PrototypeInfo>(PROTOTYPE_INFO_TYPE,
369  AllocationType::kOld);
370  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
371  result->set_prototype_users(Smi::zero());
372  result->set_registry_slot(PrototypeInfo::UNREGISTERED);
373  result->set_bit_field(0);
374  result->set_module_namespace(*undefined_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
375  for (int i = 0; i < PrototypeInfo::kCachedHandlerCount; i++) {
376  result->set_cached_handler(i, Smi::zero(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
377  }
378  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
379 }

381 DirectHandle<EnumCache> Factory::NewEnumCache(DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys,
382  DirectHandle<FixedArray> indices,
383  AllocationType allocation) {
384  DCHECK(allocation == AllocationType::kOld ||
385  allocation == AllocationType::kSharedOld);
386  DCHECK_EQ(allocation == AllocationType::kSharedOld,
387  HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(*keys) &&
388  HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(*indices));
389  auto result = NewStructInternal<EnumCache>(ENUM_CACHE_TYPE, allocation);
390  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
391  result->set_keys(*keys);
392  result->set_indices(*indices);
393  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
394 }

419 DirectHandle<PropertyArray> Factory::NewPropertyArray(
420  int length, AllocationType allocation) {
421  DCHECK_LE(0, length);
422  if (length == 0) return empty_property_array();
423  Tagged<HeapObject> result = AllocateRawFixedArray(length, allocation);
424  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
425  result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *property_array_map(),
426  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
427  Tagged<PropertyArray> array = Cast<PropertyArray>(result);
428  array->initialize_length(length);
429  MemsetTagged(array->data_start(), read_only_roots().undefined_value(),
430  length);
431  return direct_handle(array, isolate());
432 }
433 
434 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> Factory::TryNewFixedArray(
435  int length, AllocationType allocation_type) {
436  DCHECK_LE(0, length);
437  if (length == 0) return empty_fixed_array();
438 
439  int size = FixedArray::SizeFor(length);
440  Heap* heap = isolate()->heap();
441  AllocationResult allocation = heap->AllocateRaw(size, allocation_type);
442  Tagged<HeapObject> result;
443  if (!allocation.To(&result)) return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
444  if ((size > heap->MaxRegularHeapObjectSize(allocation_type)) &&
445  v8_flags.use_marking_progress_bar) {
446  LargePageMetadata::FromHeapObject(result)
447  ->marking_progress_tracker()
448  .Enable(size);
449  }
450  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
451  result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *fixed_array_map(),
452  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
453  Tagged<FixedArray> array = Cast<FixedArray>(result);
454  array->set_length(length);
455  MemsetTagged(array->RawFieldOfFirstElement(), *undefined_value(), length);
456  return handle(array, isolate());
457 }

459 Handle<FeedbackVector> Factory::NewFeedbackVector(
460  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
461  DirectHandle<ClosureFeedbackCellArray> closure_feedback_cell_array,
462  DirectHandle<FeedbackCell> parent_feedback_cell) {
463  int length = shared->feedback_metadata()->slot_count();
464  DCHECK_LE(0, length);
465  int size = FeedbackVector::SizeFor(length);
466 
467  Tagged<FeedbackVector> vector =
468  Cast<FeedbackVector>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
469  size, AllocationType::kOld, *feedback_vector_map()));
470  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
471  vector->set_shared_function_info(*shared);
472  vector->set_length(length);
473  vector->set_invocation_count(0);
474  vector->set_invocation_count_before_stable(0);
475  vector->reset_osr_state();
476  vector->reset_flags();
477 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
478  vector->set_maybe_optimized_code(ClearedValue(isolate()));
479  vector->set_log_next_execution(v8_flags.log_function_events);
480 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
481  vector->set_closure_feedback_cell_array(*closure_feedback_cell_array);
482  vector->set_parent_feedback_cell(*parent_feedback_cell);
483 
484  // TODO(leszeks): Initialize based on the feedback metadata.
485  MemsetTagged(ObjectSlot(vector->slots_start()), *undefined_value(), length);
486  return handle(vector, isolate());
487 }

489 DirectHandle<EmbedderDataArray> Factory::NewEmbedderDataArray(int length) {
490  DCHECK_LE(0, length);
491  int size = EmbedderDataArray::SizeFor(length);
492  Tagged<EmbedderDataArray> array =
493  Cast<EmbedderDataArray>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
494  size, AllocationType::kYoung, *embedder_data_array_map()));
495  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
496  array->set_length(length);
497 
498  if (length > 0) {
499  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
500  // TODO(v8): consider initializing embedded data array with Smi::zero().
501  EmbedderDataSlot(array, i).Initialize(*undefined_value());
502  }
503  }
504  return direct_handle(array, isolate());
505 }

507 DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> Factory::NewFixedDoubleArrayWithHoles(int length) {
508  DCHECK_LE(0, length);
509  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> array = NewFixedDoubleArray(length);
510  if (length > 0) {
511  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(array)->FillWithHoles(0, length);
512  }
513  return array;
514 }
515 
516 template <typename T>
517 Handle<T> Factory::AllocateSmallOrderedHashTable(DirectHandle<Map> map,
518  int capacity,
519  AllocationType allocation) {
520  // Capacity must be a power of two, since we depend on being able
521  // to divide and multiple by 2 (kLoadFactor) to derive capacity
522  // from number of buckets. If we decide to change kLoadFactor
523  // to something other than 2, capacity should be stored as another
524  // field of this object.
525  DCHECK_EQ(T::kLoadFactor, 2);
526  capacity =
527  base::bits::RoundUpToPowerOfTwo32(std::max({T::kMinCapacity, capacity}));
528  capacity = std::min({capacity, T::kMaxCapacity});
529 
530  DCHECK_LT(0, capacity);
531  DCHECK_EQ(0, capacity % T::kLoadFactor);
532 
533  int size = T::SizeFor(capacity);
534  Tagged<HeapObject> result =
535  AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(size, allocation, *map);
536  Handle<T> table(Cast<T>(result), isolate());
537  table->Initialize(isolate(), capacity);
538  return table;
539 }
540 
541 Handle<SmallOrderedHashSet> Factory::NewSmallOrderedHashSet(
542  int capacity, AllocationType allocation) {
543  return AllocateSmallOrderedHashTable<SmallOrderedHashSet>(
544  small_ordered_hash_set_map(), capacity, allocation);
545 }

547 Handle<SmallOrderedHashMap> Factory::NewSmallOrderedHashMap(

549  return AllocateSmallOrderedHashTable<SmallOrderedHashMap>(
550  small_ordered_hash_map_map(), capacity, allocation);
551 }
552 
553 Handle<SmallOrderedNameDictionary> Factory::NewSmallOrderedNameDictionary(
554  int capacity, AllocationType allocation) {
555  Handle<SmallOrderedNameDictionary> dict =
556  AllocateSmallOrderedHashTable<SmallOrderedNameDictionary>(
557  small_ordered_name_dictionary_map(), capacity, allocation);
558  dict->SetHash(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel);
559  return dict;
560 }

591 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary>
592 Factory::CreateCanonicalEmptySwissNameDictionary() {
593  // This function is only supposed to be used to create the canonical empty
594  // version and should not be used afterwards.

596  RootIndex::kEmptySwissPropertyDictionary));

613 // Internalized strings are created in the old generation (data space).
614 Handle<String> Factory::InternalizeUtf8String(base::Vector<const char> string) {
615  base::Vector<const uint8_t> utf8_data =
616  base::Vector<const uint8_t>::cast(string);
617  Utf8Decoder decoder(utf8_data);
618  if (decoder.is_ascii()) return InternalizeString(utf8_data);
619  if (decoder.is_one_byte()) {
620  std::unique_ptr<uint8_t[]> buffer(new uint8_t[decoder.utf16_length()]);
621  decoder.Decode(buffer.get(), utf8_data);
622  return InternalizeString(
623  base::Vector<const uint8_t>(buffer.get(), decoder.utf16_length()));
624  }
625  std::unique_ptr<uint16_t[]> buffer(new uint16_t[decoder.utf16_length()]);
626  decoder.Decode(buffer.get(), utf8_data);
627  return InternalizeString(
628  base::Vector<const base::uc16>(buffer.get(), decoder.utf16_length()));
629 }
630 
631 template <typename SeqString, template <typename> typename HandleType>
632  requires(
633  std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<SeqString>, DirectHandle<SeqString>>)
634 Handle<String> Factory::InternalizeSubString(HandleType<SeqString> string,
635  uint32_t from, uint32_t length,
636  bool convert_encoding) {
637  // Callers should handle the empty and one-char case themselves.
638  DCHECK_GT(length, 1);
639  DCHECK_IMPLIES(from == 0, length != string->length());
640  SeqSubStringKey<SeqString> key(isolate(), string, from, length,
641  convert_encoding);
642  return InternalizeStringWithKey(&key);
643 }

658 namespace {
659 void ThrowInvalidEncodedStringBytes(Isolate* isolate, MessageTemplate message) {
660 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
661  DCHECK(message == MessageTemplate::kWasmTrapStringInvalidWtf8 ||
662  message == MessageTemplate::kWasmTrapStringInvalidUtf8);
663  DirectHandle<JSObject> error_obj =
664  isolate->factory()->NewWasmRuntimeError(message);
665  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, error_obj,
666  isolate->factory()->wasm_uncatchable_symbol(),
667  isolate->factory()->true_value(), NONE);
668  isolate->Throw(*error_obj);
669 #else
670  // The default in JS-land is to use Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8, which never
671  // throws an error, so if there is no WebAssembly compiled in we'll never
672  // get here.
673  UNREACHABLE();
674 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
675 }
676 
677 template <typename Decoder, typename PeekBytes>
678 MaybeHandle<String> NewStringFromBytes(Isolate* isolate, PeekBytes peek_bytes,
679  AllocationType allocation,
680  MessageTemplate message) {
681  Decoder decoder(peek_bytes());
682  if (decoder.is_invalid()) {
683  if (message != MessageTemplate::kNone) {
684  ThrowInvalidEncodedStringBytes(isolate, message);
685  }
686  return MaybeHandle<String>();
687  }
688 
689  if (decoder.utf16_length() == 0) return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
690 
691  if (decoder.is_one_byte()) {
692  if (decoder.utf16_length() == 1) {
693  uint8_t codepoint;
694  decoder.Decode(&codepoint, peek_bytes());
695  return isolate->factory()->LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(codepoint);
696  }
697  // Allocate string.
698  Handle<SeqOneByteString> result;
699  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result,
700  isolate->factory()->NewRawOneByteString(
701  decoder.utf16_length(), allocation));
702 
703  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
704  decoder.Decode(result->GetChars(no_gc), peek_bytes());
705  return result;
706  }
707 
708  // Allocate string.
709  Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result;
710  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result,
711  isolate->factory()->NewRawTwoByteString(
712  decoder.utf16_length(), allocation));
713 
714  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
715  decoder.Decode(result->GetChars(no_gc), peek_bytes());
716  return result;
717 }
718 
719 template <typename PeekBytes>
720 MaybeHandle<String> NewStringFromUtf8Variant(Isolate* isolate,
721  PeekBytes peek_bytes,
722  unibrow::Utf8Variant utf8_variant,
723  AllocationType allocation) {
724  switch (utf8_variant) {
725  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8:
726  return NewStringFromBytes<Utf8Decoder>(isolate, peek_bytes, allocation,
727  MessageTemplate::kNone);
728 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
729  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8:
730  return NewStringFromBytes<StrictUtf8Decoder>(
731  isolate, peek_bytes, allocation,
732  MessageTemplate::kWasmTrapStringInvalidUtf8);
733  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap:
734  return NewStringFromBytes<StrictUtf8Decoder>(
735  isolate, peek_bytes, allocation, MessageTemplate::kNone);
736  case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8:
737  return NewStringFromBytes<Wtf8Decoder>(
738  isolate, peek_bytes, allocation,
739  MessageTemplate::kWasmTrapStringInvalidWtf8);
740 #endif
741  }
742 }
743 
744 } // namespace
745 
746 MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8(
747  base::Vector<const uint8_t> string, unibrow::Utf8Variant utf8_variant,
748  AllocationType allocation) {
749  if (string.size() > kMaxInt) {
750  // The Utf8Decode can't handle longer inputs, and we couldn't create
751  // strings from them anyway.
752  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate(), NewInvalidStringLengthError());
753  }
754  auto peek_bytes = [&]() -> base::Vector<const uint8_t> { return string; };
755  return NewStringFromUtf8Variant(isolate(), peek_bytes, utf8_variant,
756  allocation);
757 }
758 
759 MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8(base::Vector<const char> string,
760  AllocationType allocation) {
761  return NewStringFromUtf8(base::Vector<const uint8_t>::cast(string),
762  unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8, allocation);
763 }
764 
765 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
766 MaybeDirectHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8(
767  DirectHandle<WasmArray> array, uint32_t start, uint32_t end,
768  unibrow::Utf8Variant utf8_variant, AllocationType allocation) {
769  DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(uint8_t), WasmArray::DecodeElementSizeFromMap(array->map()));
770  DCHECK_LE(start, end);
771  DCHECK_LE(end, array->length());
772  // {end - start} can never be more than what the Utf8Decoder can handle.
773  static_assert(WasmArray::MaxLength(sizeof(uint8_t)) <= kMaxInt);
774  auto peek_bytes = [&]() -> base::Vector<const uint8_t> {
775  const uint8_t* contents =
776  reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(array->ElementAddress(0));
777  return {contents + start, end - start};
778  };
779  return NewStringFromUtf8Variant(isolate(), peek_bytes, utf8_variant,
780  allocation);
781 }
782 
783 MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8(
784  DirectHandle<ByteArray> array, uint32_t start, uint32_t end,
785  unibrow::Utf8Variant utf8_variant, AllocationType allocation) {
786  DCHECK_LE(start, end);
787  DCHECK_LE(end, array->length());
788  // {end - start} can never be more than what the Utf8Decoder can handle.
789  static_assert(ByteArray::kMaxLength <= kMaxInt);
790  auto peek_bytes = [&]() -> base::Vector<const uint8_t> {
791  const uint8_t* contents = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(array->begin());
792  return {contents + start, end - start};
793  };
794  return NewStringFromUtf8Variant(isolate(), peek_bytes, utf8_variant,
795  allocation);
796 }

798 namespace {
799 struct Wtf16Decoder {
800  int length_;
801  bool is_one_byte_;
802  explicit Wtf16Decoder(base::Vector<const uint16_t> data)
803  : length_(data.length()),
804  is_one_byte_(String::IsOneByte(data.begin(), length_)) {}
805  bool is_invalid() const { return false; }
806  bool is_one_byte() const { return is_one_byte_; }
807  int utf16_length() const { return length_; }
808  template <typename Char>
809  void Decode(Char* out, base::Vector<const uint16_t> data) {
810  CopyChars(out, data.begin(), length_);
811  }
812 };
813 } // namespace
814 
815 MaybeDirectHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf16(
816  DirectHandle<WasmArray> array, uint32_t start, uint32_t end,
817  AllocationType allocation) {
818  DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(uint16_t),
819  WasmArray::DecodeElementSizeFromMap(array->map()));
820  DCHECK_LE(start, end);
821  DCHECK_LE(end, array->length());
822  // {end - start} can never be more than what the Utf8Decoder can handle.
823  static_assert(WasmArray::MaxLength(sizeof(uint16_t)) <= kMaxInt);
824  auto peek_bytes = [&]() -> base::Vector<const uint16_t> {
825  const uint16_t* contents =
826  reinterpret_cast<const uint16_t*>(array->ElementAddress(0));
827  return {contents + start, end - start};
828  };
829  return NewStringFromBytes<Wtf16Decoder>(isolate(), peek_bytes, allocation,
830  MessageTemplate::kNone);
831 }
832 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
833 
834 MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8SubString(
835  Handle<SeqOneByteString> str, int begin, int length,
836  AllocationType allocation) {
837  base::Vector<const uint8_t> utf8_data;
838  {
839  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
840  utf8_data =
841  base::Vector<const uint8_t>(str->GetChars(no_gc) + begin, length);
842  }
843  Utf8Decoder decoder(utf8_data);
844 
845  if (length == 1) {
846  uint16_t t;
847  // Decode even in the case of length 1 since it can be a bad character.
848  decoder.Decode(&t, utf8_data);
849  return LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(t);
850  }
851 
852  if (decoder.is_ascii()) {
853  // If the string is ASCII, we can just make a substring.
854  // TODO(v8): the allocation flag is ignored in this case.
855  return NewSubString(str, begin, begin + length);
856  }
857 
858  DCHECK_GT(decoder.utf16_length(), 0);
859 
860  if (decoder.is_one_byte()) {
861  // Allocate string.
862  Handle<SeqOneByteString> result;
863  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
864  isolate(), result,
865  NewRawOneByteString(decoder.utf16_length(), allocation));
866  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
867  // Update pointer references, since the original string may have moved after
868  // allocation.
869  utf8_data =
870  base::Vector<const uint8_t>(str->GetChars(no_gc) + begin, length);
871  decoder.Decode(result->GetChars(no_gc), utf8_data);
872  return result;
873  }
874 
875  // Allocate string.
876  Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result;
877  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
878  isolate(), result,
879  NewRawTwoByteString(decoder.utf16_length(), allocation));
880 
881  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
882  // Update pointer references, since the original string may have moved after
883  // allocation.
884  utf8_data = base::Vector<const uint8_t>(str->GetChars(no_gc) + begin, length);
885  decoder.Decode(result->GetChars(no_gc), utf8_data);
886  return result;
887 }
888 
889 MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromTwoByte(const base::uc16* string,
890  int length,
891  AllocationType allocation) {
892  DCHECK_NE(allocation, AllocationType::kReadOnly);
893  if (length == 0) return empty_string();
894  if (String::IsOneByte(string, length)) {
895  if (length == 1) return LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(string[0]);
896  Handle<SeqOneByteString> result;
897  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate(), result,
898  NewRawOneByteString(length, allocation));
899  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
900  CopyChars(result->GetChars(no_gc), string, length);
901  return result;
902  } else {
903  Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result;
904  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate(), result,
905  NewRawTwoByteString(length, allocation));
906  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
907  CopyChars(result->GetChars(no_gc), string, length);
908  return result;
909  }
910 }
911 
912 MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromTwoByte(
913  base::Vector<const base::uc16> string, AllocationType allocation) {
914  return NewStringFromTwoByte(string.begin(), string.length(), allocation);
915 }

917 MaybeDirectHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromTwoByte(

919  return NewStringFromTwoByte(string->data(), static_cast<int>(string->size()),
920  allocation);

938 DirectHandle<String> Factory::NewInternalizedStringImpl(
939  DirectHandle<String> string, int len, uint32_t hash_field) {
940  if (string->IsOneByteRepresentation()) {

945  return result;
946  }
947

949  AllocateRawTwoByteInternalizedString(len, hash_field);

951  String::WriteToFlat(*string, result->GetChars(no_gc), 0, len);
952  return result;

954 
955 StringTransitionStrategy Factory::ComputeInternalizationStrategyForString(
956  DirectHandle<String> string, MaybeDirectHandle<Map>* internalized_map) {
957  // The serializer requires internalized strings to be in ReadOnlySpace s.t.
958  // other objects referencing the string can be allocated in RO space
959  // themselves.
960  if (isolate()->enable_ro_allocation_for_snapshot() &&
961  isolate()->serializer_enabled()) {
962  return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
963  }
964  // Do not internalize young strings in-place: This allows us to ignore both
965  // string table and stub cache on scavenges.
966  if (HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*string)) {
967  return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
968  }
969  // If the string table is shared, we need to copy if the string is not already
970  // in the shared heap.
971  if (v8_flags.shared_string_table && !HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(*string)) {
972  return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
973  }
974  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(internalized_map);
975  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
976  // This method may be called concurrently, so snapshot the map from the input
977  // string instead of the calling IsType methods on HeapObject, which would
978  // reload the map each time.
979  Tagged<Map> map = string->map();
980  *internalized_map = GetInPlaceInternalizedStringMap(map);
981  if (!internalized_map->is_null()) {
982  return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
983  }
984  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsInternalizedString(map)) {
985  return StringTransitionStrategy::kAlreadyTransitioned;
986  }
987  return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
988 }
989 
990 template <class StringClass>
991 DirectHandle<StringClass> Factory::InternalizeExternalString(
992  DirectHandle<String> string) {
993  DirectHandle<Map> map =
994  GetInPlaceInternalizedStringMap(string->map()).ToHandleChecked();
995  Tagged<StringClass> external_string =
996  Cast<StringClass>(New(map, AllocationType::kOld));
997  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
998  external_string->InitExternalPointerFields(isolate());
999  Tagged<StringClass> cast_string = Cast<StringClass>(*string);
1000  external_string->set_length(cast_string->length());
1001  external_string->set_raw_hash_field(cast_string->raw_hash_field());
1002  external_string->SetResource(isolate(), nullptr);
1003  isolate()->heap()->RegisterExternalString(external_string);
1004  return direct_handle(external_string, isolate());
1005 }
1006 
1007 template DirectHandle<ExternalOneByteString> Factory::InternalizeExternalString<
1008  ExternalOneByteString>(DirectHandle<String>);
1009 template DirectHandle<ExternalTwoByteString> Factory::InternalizeExternalString<
1010  ExternalTwoByteString>(DirectHandle<String>);
1011 
1012 StringTransitionStrategy Factory::ComputeSharingStrategyForString(
1013  DirectHandle<String> string, MaybeDirectHandle<Map>* shared_map) {
1014  DCHECK(v8_flags.shared_string_table);
1015  // TODO(pthier): Avoid copying LO-space strings. Update page flags instead.
1016  if (!HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(*string)) {
1017  return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
1018  }
1019  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(shared_map);
1020  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1021  InstanceType instance_type = string->map()->instance_type();
1022  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsSharedString(instance_type)) {
1023  return StringTransitionStrategy::kAlreadyTransitioned;
1024  }
1025  switch (instance_type) {
1026  case SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1027  *shared_map = shared_seq_two_byte_string_map();
1028  return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1029  case SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1030  *shared_map = shared_seq_one_byte_string_map();
1031  return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1032  case EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1033  *shared_map = shared_external_two_byte_string_map();
1034  return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1035  case EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1036  *shared_map = shared_external_one_byte_string_map();
1037  return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1038  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1039  *shared_map = shared_uncached_external_two_byte_string_map();
1040  return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1041  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1042  *shared_map = shared_uncached_external_one_byte_string_map();
1043  return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1044  default:
1045  return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
1046  }
1047 }
1048 
1049 DirectHandle<String> Factory::NewSurrogatePairString(uint16_t lead,
1050  uint16_t trail) {
1051  DCHECK_GE(lead, 0xD800);
1052  DCHECK_LE(lead, 0xDBFF);
1053  DCHECK_GE(trail, 0xDC00);
1054  DCHECK_LE(trail, 0xDFFF);
1055 
1056  DirectHandle<SeqTwoByteString> str =
1057  isolate()->factory()->NewRawTwoByteString(2).ToHandleChecked();
1058  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1059  base::uc16* dest = str->GetChars(no_gc);
1060  dest[0] = lead;
1061  dest[1] = trail;
1062  return str;
1063 }
1064 
1065 Handle<String> Factory::NewCopiedSubstring(DirectHandle<String> str,
1066  uint32_t begin, uint32_t length) {
1067  DCHECK(str->IsFlat()); // Callers must flatten.
1068  DCHECK_GT(length, 0); // Callers must handle empty string.
1069  bool one_byte;
1070  {
1071  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1072  String::FlatContent flat = str->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
1073  if (flat.IsOneByte()) {
1074  one_byte = true;
1075  } else {
1076  one_byte = String::IsOneByte(flat.ToUC16Vector().data() + begin, length);
1077  }
1078  }
1079  if (one_byte) {
1080  Handle<SeqOneByteString> result =
1081  NewRawOneByteString(length).ToHandleChecked();
1082  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1083  uint8_t* dest = result->GetChars(no_gc);
1084  String::WriteToFlat(*str, dest, begin, length);
1085  return result;
1086  } else {
1087  Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result =
1088  NewRawTwoByteString(length).ToHandleChecked();
1089  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1090  base::uc16* dest = result->GetChars(no_gc);
1091  String::WriteToFlat(*str, dest, begin, length);
1092  return result;
1093  }
1094 }
1095 
1096 Handle<String> Factory::NewProperSubString(DirectHandle<String> str,
1097  uint32_t begin, uint32_t end) {
1098 #if VERIFY_HEAP
1099  if (v8_flags.verify_heap) str->StringVerify(isolate());
1100 #endif
1101  DCHECK_LE(begin, str->length());
1102  DCHECK_LE(end, str->length());
1103 
1104  str = String::Flatten(isolate(), str);
1105 
1106  if (begin >= end) return empty_string();
1107  uint32_t length = end - begin;
1108 
1109  if (length == 1) {
1110  return LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(str->Get(begin));
1111  }
1112  if (length == 2) {
1113  // Optimization for 2-byte strings often used as keys in a decompression
1114  // dictionary. Check whether we already have the string in the string
1115  // table to prevent creation of many unnecessary strings.
1116  uint16_t c1 = str->Get(begin);
1117  uint16_t c2 = str->Get(begin + 1);
1118  return MakeOrFindTwoCharacterString(c1, c2);
1119  }
1120 
1121  if (!v8_flags.string_slices || length < SlicedString::kMinLength) {
1122  return NewCopiedSubstring(str, begin, length);
1123  }
1124 
1125  int offset = begin;
1126 
1127  if (IsSlicedString(*str)) {
1128  auto slice = Cast<SlicedString>(str);
1129  str = direct_handle(slice->parent(), isolate());
1130  offset += slice->offset();
1131  }
1132  if (IsThinString(*str)) {
1133  auto thin = Cast<ThinString>(str);
1134  str = direct_handle(thin->actual(), isolate());
1135  }
1136 
1137  DCHECK(IsSeqString(*str) || IsExternalString(*str));
1138  DirectHandle<Map> map = str->IsOneByteRepresentation()
1139  ? sliced_one_byte_string_map()
1140  : sliced_two_byte_string_map();
1141  Tagged<SlicedString> slice =
1142  Cast<SlicedString>(New(map, AllocationType::kYoung));
1143  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1144  slice->set_raw_hash_field(String::kEmptyHashField);
1145  slice->set_length(length);
1146  slice->set_parent(*str);
1147  slice->set_offset(offset);
1148  return handle(slice, isolate());
1149 }
1150 
1151 MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewExternalStringFromOneByte(
1152  const ExternalOneByteString::Resource* resource) {
1153  size_t length = resource->length();
1154  if (length > static_cast<size_t>(String::kMaxLength)) {
1155  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate(), NewInvalidStringLengthError());
1156  }
1157  if (length == 0) return empty_string();
1158 
1159  DirectHandle<Map> map = resource->IsCacheable()
1160  ? external_one_byte_string_map()
1161  : uncached_external_one_byte_string_map();
1162  Tagged<ExternalOneByteString> external_string =
1163  Cast<ExternalOneByteString>(New(map, AllocationType::kOld));
1164  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1165  external_string->InitExternalPointerFields(isolate());
1166  external_string->set_length(static_cast<int>(length));
1167  external_string->set_raw_hash_field(String::kEmptyHashField);
1168  external_string->SetResource(isolate(), resource);
1169 
1170  isolate()->heap()->RegisterExternalString(external_string);
1171 
1172  return Handle<String>(external_string, isolate());
1173 }
1174 
1175 MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewExternalStringFromTwoByte(
1176  const ExternalTwoByteString::Resource* resource) {
1177  size_t length = resource->length();
1178  if (length > static_cast<size_t>(String::kMaxLength)) {
1179  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate(), NewInvalidStringLengthError());
1180  }
1181  if (length == 0) return empty_string();
1182 
1183  DirectHandle<Map> map = resource->IsCacheable()
1184  ? external_two_byte_string_map()
1185  : uncached_external_two_byte_string_map();
1186  Tagged<ExternalTwoByteString> string =
1187  Cast<ExternalTwoByteString>(New(map, AllocationType::kOld));
1188  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1189  string->InitExternalPointerFields(isolate());
1190  string->set_length(static_cast<int>(length));
1191  string->set_raw_hash_field(String::kEmptyHashField);
1192  string->SetResource(isolate(), resource);
1193 
1194  isolate()->heap()->RegisterExternalString(string);
1195 
1196  return Handle<ExternalTwoByteString>(string, isolate());
1197 }

1199 DirectHandle<JSStringIterator> Factory::NewJSStringIterator(
1200  Handle<String> string) {
1201  DirectHandle<Map> map(
1202  isolate()->native_context()->initial_string_iterator_map(), isolate());
1203  DirectHandle<String> flat_string = String::Flatten(isolate(), string);
1204  DirectHandle<JSStringIterator> iterator =
1205  Cast<JSStringIterator>(NewJSObjectFromMap(map));
1206 
1207  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1208  Tagged<JSStringIterator> raw = *iterator;
1209  raw->set_string(*flat_string);
1210  raw->set_index(0);
1211  return iterator;
1212 }

1214 Tagged<Symbol> Factory::NewSymbolInternal(AllocationType allocation) {
1215  DCHECK(allocation != AllocationType::kYoung);
1216  // Statically ensure that it is safe to allocate symbols in paged spaces.
1217  static_assert(sizeof(Symbol) <= kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize);
1218 
1219  Tagged<Symbol> symbol = Cast<Symbol>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1220  sizeof(Symbol), allocation, read_only_roots().symbol_map()));
1221  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1222  // Generate a random hash value.
1223  int hash = isolate()->GenerateIdentityHash(Name::HashBits::kMax);
1224  symbol->set_raw_hash_field(
1225  Name::CreateHashFieldValue(hash, Name::HashFieldType::kHash));
1226  if (isolate()->read_only_heap()->roots_init_complete()) {
1227  symbol->set_description(read_only_roots().undefined_value(),
1228  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1229  } else {
1230  // Can't use setter during bootstrapping as its typecheck tries to access
1231  // the roots table before it is initialized.
1232  symbol->description_.store(&*symbol, read_only_roots().undefined_value(),
1233  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1234  }
1235  symbol->set_flags(0);
1236  DCHECK(!symbol->is_private());
1237  return symbol;
1238 }
1239 
1240 Handle<Symbol> Factory::NewSymbol(AllocationType allocation) {
1241  return handle(NewSymbolInternal(allocation), isolate());
1242 }

1244 Handle<Symbol> Factory::NewPrivateSymbol(AllocationType allocation) {
1245  DCHECK(allocation != AllocationType::kYoung);
1246  Tagged<Symbol> symbol = NewSymbolInternal(allocation);
1247  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1248  symbol->set_is_private(true);
1249  return handle(symbol, isolate());
1250 }

1252 DirectHandle<Symbol> Factory::NewPrivateNameSymbol(DirectHandle<String> name) {

1259 
1260 Tagged<Context> Factory::NewContextInternal(DirectHandle<Map> map, int size,
1261  int variadic_part_length,
1262  AllocationType allocation) {
1263  DCHECK_LE(Context::kTodoHeaderSize, size);
1264  DCHECK(IsAligned(size, kTaggedSize));
1265  DCHECK_LE(Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS, variadic_part_length);
1266  DCHECK_LE(Context::SizeFor(variadic_part_length), size);
1267 
1268  Tagged<HeapObject> result =
1269  allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(size,
1270  allocation);
1271  result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map);
1272  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1273  Tagged<Context> context = Cast<Context>(result);
1274  context->set_length(variadic_part_length);
1275  DCHECK_EQ(context->SizeFromMap(*map), size);
1276  if (size > Context::kTodoHeaderSize) {
1277  ObjectSlot start = context->RawField(Context::kTodoHeaderSize);
1278  ObjectSlot end = context->RawField(size);
1279  size_t slot_count = end - start;
1280  MemsetTagged(start, *undefined_value(), slot_count);
1281  }
1282  return context;
1283 }
1284 
1285 // Creates new maps and new native context and wires them up.
1286 //
1287 // +-+------------->|NativeContext|
1288 // | | |
1289 // | | map
1290 // | | v
1291 // | | |context_map| <Map(NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE)>
1292 // | | | |
1293 // | +--native_context--+ map
1294 // | v
1295 // | +------->|contextful_meta_map| <Map(MAP_TYPE)>
1296 // | | | |
1297 // | +-----map-----+ |
1298 // | |
1299 // +-----native_context-----+
1300 //
1301 Handle<NativeContext> Factory::NewNativeContext() {
1302  // All maps that belong to this new native context will have this meta map.
1303  // The native context does not exist yet, so create the map as contextless
1304  // for now.
1305  DirectHandle<Map> contextful_meta_map =
1306  NewContextlessMap(MAP_TYPE, Map::kSize);
1307  contextful_meta_map->set_map(isolate(), *contextful_meta_map);
1308 
1309  DirectHandle<Map> context_map = NewMapWithMetaMap(
1310  contextful_meta_map, NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE, kVariableSizeSentinel);
1311 
1312  if (v8_flags.log_maps) {
1313  LOG(isolate(),
1314  MapEvent("NewNativeContext", isolate()->factory()->meta_map(),
1315  contextful_meta_map, "contextful meta map"));
1316  LOG(isolate(),
1317  MapEvent("NewNativeContext", isolate()->factory()->meta_map(),
1318  context_map, "native context map"));
1319  }
1320 
1321  Tagged<NativeContext> context = Cast<NativeContext>(NewContextInternal(
1322  context_map, NativeContext::kSize, NativeContext::NATIVE_CONTEXT_SLOTS,
1323  AllocationType::kOld));
1324  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1325  contextful_meta_map->set_native_context(context);
1326  context_map->set_native_context(context);
1327  context->set_meta_map(*contextful_meta_map);
1328  context->set_scope_info(*native_scope_info());
1329  context->set_previous(Context());
1330  context->set_extension(*undefined_value());
1331  context->set_errors_thrown(Smi::zero());
1332  context->set_is_wasm_js_installed(Smi::zero());
1333  context->set_is_wasm_jspi_installed(Smi::zero());
1334  context->set_math_random_index(Smi::zero());
1335  context->set_serialized_objects(*empty_fixed_array());
1336  context->init_microtask_queue(isolate(), nullptr);
1337  context->set_retained_maps(*empty_weak_array_list());
1338  return handle(context, isolate());
1339 }

1341 DirectHandle<Context> Factory::NewScriptContext(
1342  DirectHandle<NativeContext> outer, DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info) {
1343  DCHECK(scope_info->is_script_scope());
1344  int variadic_part_length = scope_info->ContextLength();
1345  Tagged<Context> context =
1346  NewContextInternal(direct_handle(outer->script_context_map(), isolate()),
1347  Context::SizeFor(variadic_part_length),
1348  variadic_part_length, AllocationType::kOld);
1349  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1350  context->set_scope_info(*scope_info);
1351  context->set_previous(*outer);
1352  DCHECK(context->IsScriptContext());
1353  return direct_handle(context, isolate());
1354 }

1378 DirectHandle<Context> Factory::NewFunctionContext(
1379  DirectHandle<Context> outer, DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info) {
1380  DirectHandle<Map> map;
1381  switch (scope_info->scope_type()) {
1382  case EVAL_SCOPE:
1383  map = isolate()->eval_context_map();
1384  break;
1385  case FUNCTION_SCOPE:
1386  map = isolate()->function_context_map();
1387  break;
1388  default:
1389  UNREACHABLE();
1390  }
1391  int variadic_part_length = scope_info->ContextLength();
1392  Tagged<Context> context =
1393  NewContextInternal(map, Context::SizeFor(variadic_part_length),
1394  variadic_part_length, AllocationType::kYoung);
1395  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1396  context->set_scope_info(*scope_info);
1397  context->set_previous(*outer);
1398  return direct_handle(context, isolate());
1399 }

1401 #if V8_SINGLE_GENERATION_BOOL
1402 #define DCHECK_NEWLY_ALLOCATED_OBJECT_IS_YOUNG(isolate, object)
1403 #elif V8_ENABLE_STICKY_MARK_BITS_BOOL
1404 #define DCHECK_NEWLY_ALLOCATED_OBJECT_IS_YOUNG(isolate, object) \
1405  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!isolate->heap()->incremental_marking()->IsMajorMarking(), \
1406  HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(object))
1407 #else
1408 #define DCHECK_NEWLY_ALLOCATED_OBJECT_IS_YOUNG(isolate, object) \
1409  DCHECK(HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(object))
1410 #endif

1412 DirectHandle<Context> Factory::NewCatchContext(
1413  DirectHandle<Context> previous, DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info,
1414  DirectHandle<Object> thrown_object) {
1415  DCHECK_EQ(scope_info->scope_type(), CATCH_SCOPE);
1416  static_assert(Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS == Context::THROWN_OBJECT_INDEX);
1417  // TODO(ishell): Take the details from CatchContext class.
1418  int variadic_part_length = Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS + 1;
1419  Tagged<Context> context = NewContextInternal(
1420  isolate()->catch_context_map(), Context::SizeFor(variadic_part_length),
1421  variadic_part_length, AllocationType::kYoung);
1422  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1423  DCHECK_NEWLY_ALLOCATED_OBJECT_IS_YOUNG(isolate(), context);
1424  context->set_scope_info(*scope_info, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1425  context->set_previous(*previous, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1426  context->SetNoCell(Context::THROWN_OBJECT_INDEX, *thrown_object,
1427  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1428  return direct_handle(context, isolate());
1429 }

1441  NewContextInternal(isolate()->debug_evaluate_context_map(),

1446  context->set_scope_info(*scope_info, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1447  context->set_previous(*previous, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1448  context->set_extension(*ext, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1449  if (!wrapped.is_null()) {
1450  context->SetNoCell(Context::WRAPPED_CONTEXT_INDEX, *wrapped,
1451  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);

1453  return handle(context, isolate());

1574 void Factory::ProcessNewScript(DirectHandle<Script> script,
1575  ScriptEventType script_event_type) {
1576  int script_id = script->id();
1577  if (script_id != Script::kTemporaryScriptId) {
1578  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> scripts = script_list();
1579  scripts = WeakArrayList::Append(isolate(), scripts,
1580  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(script),
1581  AllocationType::kOld);
1582  isolate()->heap()->set_script_list(*scripts);
1583  }
1584  if (IsString(script->source()) && isolate()->NeedsSourcePositions()) {
1585  Script::InitLineEnds(isolate(), script);
1586  }
1587  LOG(isolate(), ScriptEvent(script_event_type, script_id));
1588 }
1589 
1590 Handle<Script> Factory::CloneScript(DirectHandle<Script> script,
1591  DirectHandle<String> source) {
1592  int script_id = isolate()->GetNextScriptId();
1593 #ifdef V8_SCRIPTORMODULE_LEGACY_LIFETIME
1594  DirectHandle<ArrayList> list = ArrayList::New(isolate(), 0);
1595 #endif
1596  Handle<Script> new_script_handle =
1597  Cast<Script>(NewStruct(SCRIPT_TYPE, AllocationType::kOld));
1598  {
1599  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1600  Tagged<Script> new_script = *new_script_handle;
1601  const Tagged<Script> old_script = *script;
1602  new_script->set_source(*source);
1603  new_script->set_name(old_script->name());
1604  new_script->set_id(script_id);
1605  new_script->set_line_offset(old_script->line_offset());
1606  new_script->set_column_offset(old_script->column_offset());
1607  new_script->set_context_data(old_script->context_data());
1608  new_script->set_type(old_script->type());
1609  new_script->set_line_ends(Smi::zero());
1610  new_script->set_eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments(
1611  script->eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments());
1612  new_script->set_infos(*empty_weak_fixed_array(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1613  new_script->set_eval_from_position(old_script->eval_from_position());
1614  new_script->set_flags(old_script->flags());
1615  new_script->set_host_defined_options(old_script->host_defined_options());
1616  new_script->set_source_hash(*undefined_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1617  new_script->set_compiled_lazy_function_positions(*undefined_value(),
1618  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1619 #ifdef V8_SCRIPTORMODULE_LEGACY_LIFETIME
1620  new_script->set_script_or_modules(*list);
1621 #endif
1622  }
1623  ProcessNewScript(new_script_handle, ScriptEventType::kCreate);
1624  return new_script_handle;
1625 }
1626 
1627 DirectHandle<CallableTask> Factory::NewCallableTask(
1628  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> callable, DirectHandle<Context> context) {
1629  DCHECK(IsCallable(*callable));
1630  auto microtask = NewStructInternal<CallableTask>(CALLABLE_TASK_TYPE,
1631  AllocationType::kYoung);
1632  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1633  microtask->set_callable(*callable, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1634  microtask->set_context(*context, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1635 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
1636  microtask->set_continuation_preserved_embedder_data(
1637  isolate()->isolate_data()->continuation_preserved_embedder_data(),
1638  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1639 #endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
1640  return direct_handle(microtask, isolate());
1641 }

1681 DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> Factory::NewWasmTrustedInstanceData(
1682  bool shared) {

1684  Cast<WasmTrustedInstanceData>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1685  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kSize,
1686  shared ? AllocationType::kSharedTrusted : AllocationType::kTrusted,
1687  read_only_roots().wasm_trusted_instance_data_map()));
1688  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;

1690  result->clear_padding();

1697 DirectHandle<WasmDispatchTable> Factory::NewWasmDispatchTable(
1698  int length, wasm::CanonicalValueType table_type, bool shared) {
1699  CHECK_LE(length, WasmDispatchTable::kMaxLength);
1700 
1701  // TODO(jkummerow): Any chance to get a better estimate?
1702  size_t estimated_offheap_size = 0;
1703  DirectHandle<TrustedManaged<WasmDispatchTableData>> offheap_data =
1704  TrustedManaged<WasmDispatchTableData>::From(
1705  isolate(), estimated_offheap_size,
1706  std::make_shared<WasmDispatchTableData>(), shared);
1707 
1708  int bytes = WasmDispatchTable::SizeFor(length);
1709  Tagged<WasmDispatchTable> result =
1710  UncheckedCast<WasmDispatchTable>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1711  bytes,
1712  shared ? AllocationType::kSharedTrusted : AllocationType::kTrusted,
1713  read_only_roots().wasm_dispatch_table_map()));
1714  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1715  result->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());
1716  result->WriteField<int>(WasmDispatchTable::kLengthOffset, length);
1717  result->WriteField<int>(WasmDispatchTable::kCapacityOffset, length);
1718  result->set_protected_offheap_data(*offheap_data);
1719  result->set_protected_uses(*empty_protected_weak_fixed_array());
1720  result->set_table_type(table_type);
1721  for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
1722  result->Clear(i, WasmDispatchTable::kNewEntry);
1723  }
1724  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
1725 }
1726 
1727 DirectHandle<WasmTypeInfo> Factory::NewWasmTypeInfo(
1728  wasm::CanonicalValueType type, wasm::CanonicalValueType element_type,
1729  DirectHandle<Map> opt_parent, bool shared) {
1730  // We pretenure WasmTypeInfo objects for two reasons:
1731  // (1) They are referenced by Maps, which are assumed to be long-lived,
1732  // so pretenuring the WTI is a bit more efficient.
1733  // (2) The object visitors need to read the WasmTypeInfo to find tagged
1734  // fields in Wasm structs; in the middle of a GC cycle that's only
1735  // safe to do if the WTI is in old space.
1736  DirectHandleVector<Object> supertypes(isolate());
1737  if (opt_parent.is_null()) {
1738  supertypes.resize(wasm::kMinimumSupertypeArraySize, undefined_value());
1739  } else {
1740  DirectHandle<WasmTypeInfo> parent_type_info(opt_parent->wasm_type_info(),
1741  isolate());
1742  int first_undefined_index = -1;
1743  for (int i = 0; i < parent_type_info->supertypes_length(); i++) {
1744  DirectHandle<Object> supertype(parent_type_info->supertypes(i),
1745  isolate());
1746  if (IsUndefined(*supertype) && first_undefined_index == -1) {
1747  first_undefined_index = i;
1748  }
1749  supertypes.emplace_back(supertype);
1750  }
1751  if (first_undefined_index >= 0) {
1752  supertypes[first_undefined_index] = opt_parent;
1753  } else {
1754  supertypes.emplace_back(opt_parent);
1755  }
1756  }
1757  Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_type_info_map();
1758  Tagged<WasmTypeInfo> result = Cast<WasmTypeInfo>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1759  WasmTypeInfo::SizeFor(static_cast<int>(supertypes.size())),
1760  shared ? AllocationType::kSharedOld : AllocationType::kOld, map));
1761  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1762  result->set_supertypes_length(static_cast<int>(supertypes.size()));
1763  for (size_t i = 0; i < supertypes.size(); i++) {
1764  result->set_supertypes(static_cast<int>(i), *supertypes[i]);
1765  }
1766  result->set_canonical_type(type.raw_bit_field());
1767  result->set_canonical_element_type(element_type.raw_bit_field());
1768  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
1769 }

1771 DirectHandle<WasmImportData> Factory::NewWasmImportData(
1772  DirectHandle<HeapObject> callable, wasm::Suspend suspend,
1773  MaybeDirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance_data,
1774  const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig, bool shared) {
1775  Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_import_data_map();
1776  auto result = Cast<WasmImportData>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1777  map->instance_size(),
1778  shared ? AllocationType::kSharedTrusted : AllocationType::kTrusted, map));
1779  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1780  result->set_native_context(*isolate()->native_context());
1781  result->set_callable(Cast<UnionOf<Undefined, JSReceiver>>(*callable));
1782  result->set_suspend(suspend);
1783  if (instance_data.is_null()) {
1784  result->clear_instance_data();
1785  } else {
1786  result->set_instance_data(*instance_data.ToHandleChecked());
1787  }
1788  result->set_wrapper_budget(v8_flags.wasm_wrapper_tiering_budget);
1789  result->clear_call_origin();
1790  result->set_sig(sig);
1791 #if TAGGED_SIZE_8_BYTES
1792  result->set_optional_padding(0);
1793 #endif
1794  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
1795 }

1854 DirectHandle<WasmJSFunctionData> Factory::NewWasmJSFunctionData(
1855  wasm::CanonicalTypeIndex sig_index, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> callable,
1856  DirectHandle<Code> wrapper_code, DirectHandle<Map> rtt,
1857  wasm::Suspend suspend, wasm::Promise promise,
1858  std::shared_ptr<wasm::WasmImportWrapperHandle> wrapper_handle) {
1859  // TODO(clemensb): Should this be passed instead of looked up here?
1860  const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig =
1861  wasm::GetTypeCanonicalizer()->LookupFunctionSignature(sig_index);
1862  constexpr bool kShared = false;
1863  DirectHandle<WasmImportData> import_data = NewWasmImportData(
1864  callable, suspend, DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData>(), sig, kShared);
1865 
1866  DirectHandle<WasmInternalFunction> internal = NewWasmInternalFunction(
1867  import_data, -1, kShared, wrapper_handle->code_pointer());
1868  DirectHandle<WasmFuncRef> func_ref = NewWasmFuncRef(internal, rtt, kShared);
1869  import_data->SetFuncRefAsCallOrigin(*internal);
1870 
1871  // Rough guess for a wrapper that may be shared with other users of it.
1872  constexpr size_t kOffheapDataSizeEstimate = 100;
1873  constexpr bool shared = false;
1874  DirectHandle<TrustedManaged<WasmJSFunctionData::OffheapData>> offheap_data =
1875  TrustedManaged<WasmJSFunctionData::OffheapData>::From(
1876  isolate(), kOffheapDataSizeEstimate,
1877  std::make_shared<WasmJSFunctionData::OffheapData>(
1878  std::move(wrapper_handle)),
1879  shared);
1880 
1881  Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_js_function_data_map();
1882  Tagged<WasmJSFunctionData> result =
1883  Cast<WasmJSFunctionData>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1884  map->instance_size(), AllocationType::kTrusted, map));
1885  result->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());
1886  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1887  result->set_func_ref(*func_ref);
1888  result->set_internal(*internal);
1889  result->set_wrapper_code(*wrapper_code);
1890  result->set_canonical_sig_index(sig_index.index);
1891  result->set_js_promise_flags(WasmFunctionData::SuspendField::encode(suspend) |
1892  WasmFunctionData::PromiseField::encode(promise));
1893  result->set_protected_offheap_data(*offheap_data);
1894  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
1895 }

1908 
1909 DirectHandle<WasmSuspenderObject> Factory::NewWasmSuspenderObject() {
1910  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise = NewJSPromise();
1911  Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_suspender_object_map();
1912  Tagged<WasmSuspenderObject> obj =
1913  Cast<WasmSuspenderObject>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1914  map->instance_size(), AllocationType::kOld, map));
1915  auto suspender = handle(obj, isolate());
1916  // Ensure that all properties are initialized before the allocation below.
1917  suspender->init_stack(IsolateForSandbox(isolate()), nullptr);
1918  suspender->set_parent(*undefined_value());
1919  suspender->set_promise(*promise);
1920  suspender->set_resume(*undefined_value());
1921  suspender->set_reject(*undefined_value());
1922  // Instantiate the callable object which resumes this Suspender. This will be
1923  // used implicitly as the onFulfilled callback of the returned JS promise.
1924  DirectHandle<WasmResumeData> resume_data =
1925  NewWasmResumeData(suspender, wasm::OnResume::kContinue);
1926  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> resume_sfi =
1927  NewSharedFunctionInfoForWasmResume(resume_data);
1928  DirectHandle<Context> context(isolate()->native_context());
1929  DirectHandle<JSObject> resume =
1930  Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate(), resume_sfi, context}.Build();
1931 
1932  DirectHandle<WasmResumeData> reject_data =
1933  isolate()->factory()->NewWasmResumeData(suspender,
1934  wasm::OnResume::kThrow);
1935  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> reject_sfi =
1936  isolate()->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForWasmResume(reject_data);
1937  DirectHandle<JSObject> reject =
1938  Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate(), reject_sfi, context}.Build();
1939  suspender->set_resume(*resume);
1940  suspender->set_reject(*reject);
1941  return suspender;
1942 }

1944 DirectHandle<WasmExportedFunctionData> Factory::NewWasmExportedFunctionData(
1945  DirectHandle<Code> export_wrapper,
1946  DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance_data,
1947  DirectHandle<WasmFuncRef> func_ref,
1948  DirectHandle<WasmInternalFunction> internal_function,
1949  const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig, wasm::CanonicalTypeIndex type_index,
1950  int wrapper_budget, wasm::Promise promise) {
1951  int func_index = internal_function->function_index();
1952  DirectHandle<Cell> wrapper_budget_cell =
1953  NewCell(Smi::FromInt(wrapper_budget));
1954  Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_exported_function_data_map();
1955  Tagged<WasmExportedFunctionData> result =
1956  Cast<WasmExportedFunctionData>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1957  map->instance_size(), AllocationType::kTrusted, map));
1958  result->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());
1959  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1960  result->set_func_ref(*func_ref);
1961  result->set_internal(*internal_function);
1962  result->set_wrapper_code(*export_wrapper);
1963  result->set_instance_data(*instance_data);
1964  result->set_function_index(func_index);
1965  result->set_sig(sig);
1966  result->set_canonical_type_index(type_index.index);
1967  result->set_receiver_is_first_param(0);
1968  result->set_wrapper_budget(*wrapper_budget_cell);
1969  // We can't skip the write barrier because Code objects are not immovable.
1970  result->set_c_wrapper_code(*BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), Illegal),
1971  UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
1972  result->set_packed_args_size(0);
1973  result->set_js_promise_flags(
1974  WasmFunctionData::SuspendField::encode(wasm::kNoSuspend) |
1975  WasmFunctionData::PromiseField::encode(promise));
1976  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
1977 }

1979 DirectHandle<WasmCapiFunctionData> Factory::NewWasmCapiFunctionData(
1980  Address call_target, DirectHandle<Foreign> embedder_data,
1981  DirectHandle<Code> wrapper_code, DirectHandle<Map> rtt,
1982  wasm::CanonicalTypeIndex sig_index, const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig) {

1990  ->GetOrCreateHandleForNativeFunction(call_target));
1991  DirectHandle<WasmFuncRef> func_ref = NewWasmFuncRef(internal, rtt, kShared);

2008  WasmFunctionData::PromiseField::encode(wasm::kNoPromise));

2010 }

2012 Tagged<WasmArray> Factory::NewWasmArrayUninitialized(uint32_t length,
2013  DirectHandle<Map> map) {

2015  HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(*map)
2016  ? AllocationType::kSharedOld
2017  : AllocationType::kYoung);
2018  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2019  raw->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map);
2020  Tagged<WasmArray> result = Cast<WasmArray>(raw);
2021  result->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*empty_fixed_array(), kRelaxedStore);
2022  result->set_length(length);

2025 
2026 DirectHandle<WasmArray> Factory::NewWasmArray(wasm::ValueType element_type,
2027  uint32_t length,
2028  wasm::WasmValue initial_value,
2029  DirectHandle<Map> map) {
2030  Tagged<WasmArray> result = NewWasmArrayUninitialized(length, map);
2031  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2032  if (element_type.is_numeric()) {
2033  if (initial_value.zero_byte_representation()) {
2034  memset(reinterpret_cast<void*>(result->ElementAddress(0)), 0,
2035  length * element_type.value_kind_size());
2036  } else {
2037  wasm::WasmValue packed = initial_value.Packed(element_type);
2038  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2039  Address address = result->ElementAddress(i);
2040  packed.CopyTo(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(address));
2041  }
2042  }
2043  } else {
2044  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2045  result->SetTaggedElement(i, initial_value.to_ref());
2046  }
2047  }
2048  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
2049 }
2050 
2051 DirectHandle<WasmArray> Factory::NewWasmArrayFromElements(
2052  const wasm::ArrayType* type, base::Vector<wasm::WasmValue> elements,
2053  DirectHandle<Map> map) {
2054  uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(elements.size());
2055  Tagged<WasmArray> result = NewWasmArrayUninitialized(length, map);
2056  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2057  if (type->element_type().is_numeric()) {
2058  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2059  Address address = result->ElementAddress(i);
2060  elements[i]
2061  .Packed(type->element_type())
2062  .CopyTo(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(address));
2063  }
2064  } else {
2065  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2066  result->SetTaggedElement(i, elements[i].to_ref());
2067  }
2068  }
2069  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
2070 }
2071 
2072 DirectHandle<WasmArray> Factory::NewWasmArrayFromMemory(
2073  uint32_t length, DirectHandle<Map> map,
2074  wasm::CanonicalValueType element_type, Address source) {
2075  DCHECK(element_type.is_numeric());
2076  Tagged<WasmArray> result = NewWasmArrayUninitialized(length, map);
2077  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2078 #if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
2079  MemCopyAndSwitchEndianness(reinterpret_cast<void*>(result->ElementAddress(0)),
2080  reinterpret_cast<void*>(source), length,
2081  element_type.value_kind_size());
2082 #else
2083  MemCopy(reinterpret_cast<void*>(result->ElementAddress(0)),
2084  reinterpret_cast<void*>(source),
2085  length * element_type.value_kind_size());
2086 #endif
2087 
2088  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
2089 }
2090 
2091 DirectHandle<Object> Factory::NewWasmArrayFromElementSegment(
2092  DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data,
2093  DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> shared_trusted_instance_data,
2094  uint32_t segment_index, uint32_t start_offset, uint32_t length,
2095  DirectHandle<Map> map, wasm::CanonicalValueType element_type) {
2096  DCHECK(element_type.is_reference());
2097 
2098  // If the element segment has not been initialized yet, lazily initialize it
2099  // now.
2100  AccountingAllocator allocator;
2101  Zone zone(&allocator, ZONE_NAME);
2102  std::optional<MessageTemplate> opt_error = wasm::InitializeElementSegment(
2103  &zone, isolate(), trusted_instance_data, shared_trusted_instance_data,
2104  segment_index);
2105  if (opt_error.has_value()) {
2106  return direct_handle(Smi::FromEnum(opt_error.value()), isolate());
2107  }
2108 
2109  DirectHandle<FixedArray> elements = direct_handle(
2110  Cast<FixedArray>(
2111  trusted_instance_data->element_segments()->get(segment_index)),
2112  isolate());
2113 
2114  Tagged<WasmArray> result = NewWasmArrayUninitialized(length, map);
2115  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2116  if (length > 0) {
2117  isolate()->heap()->CopyRange(
2118  result, result->ElementSlot(0),
2119  elements->RawFieldOfElementAt(start_offset), length,
2120  HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(result) ? UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER
2121  : SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2122  }
2123  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
2124 }
2125 
2126 Handle<WasmStruct> Factory::NewWasmStructUninitialized(
2127  const wasm::StructType* type, DirectHandle<Map> map,
2128  AllocationType allocation) {
2129  Tagged<HeapObject> raw = AllocateRaw(WasmStruct::Size(type), allocation);
2130  raw->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map);
2131  Tagged<WasmStruct> result = Cast<WasmStruct>(raw);
2132  result->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*empty_fixed_array(), kRelaxedStore);
2133  return handle(result, isolate());
2134 }
2135 
2136 DirectHandle<WasmStruct> Factory::NewWasmStruct(const wasm::StructType* type,
2137  wasm::WasmValue* args,
2138  DirectHandle<Map> map) {
2139  Tagged<HeapObject> raw =
2140  AllocateRaw(WasmStruct::Size(type), HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(*map)
2141  ? AllocationType::kSharedOld
2142  : AllocationType::kYoung);
2143  raw->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map);
2144  Tagged<WasmStruct> result = Cast<WasmStruct>(raw);
2145  result->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*empty_fixed_array(), kRelaxedStore);
2146  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < type->field_count(); i++) {
2147  int offset = type->field_offset(i);
2148  if (type->field(i).is_numeric()) {
2149  Address address = result->RawFieldAddress(offset);
2150  args[i]
2151  .Packed(type->field(i))
2152  .CopyTo(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(address));
2153  } else {
2154  offset += WasmStruct::kHeaderSize;
2155  TaggedField<Object>::store(result, offset, *args[i].to_ref());
2156  }
2157  }
2158  return direct_handle(result, isolate());
2159 }

2275 DirectHandle<TransitionArray> Factory::NewTransitionArray(
2276  int number_of_transitions, int slack) {
2277  int capacity = TransitionArray::LengthFor(number_of_transitions + slack);
2278  DirectHandle<TransitionArray> array = Cast<TransitionArray>(
2279  NewWeakFixedArrayWithMap(read_only_roots().transition_array_map(),
2280  capacity, AllocationType::kOld));
2281  // Transition arrays are AllocationType::kOld. When black allocation is on we
2282  // have to add the transition array to the list of
2283  // encountered_transition_arrays.
2284  Heap* heap = isolate()->heap();
2285  if (heap->incremental_marking()->black_allocation()) {
2286  heap->mark_compact_collector()->AddTransitionArray(*array);
2287  }
2288  array->WeakFixedArray::set(TransitionArray::kPrototypeTransitionsIndex,
2289  Smi::zero());
2290  array->WeakFixedArray::set(TransitionArray::kSideStepTransitionsIndex,
2291  Smi::zero());
2292  array->WeakFixedArray::set(TransitionArray::kTransitionLengthIndex,
2293  Smi::FromInt(number_of_transitions));
2294  return array;
2295 }

2297 Handle<AllocationSite> Factory::NewAllocationSite(bool with_weak_next) {
2298  DirectHandle<Map> map = with_weak_next
2299  ? allocation_site_map()
2300  : allocation_site_without_weaknext_map();
2301  Handle<AllocationSite> site(
2302  Cast<AllocationSite>(New(map, AllocationType::kOld)), isolate());
2303  site->Initialize();
2304 
2305  if (with_weak_next) {
2306  // Link the site
2307  Cast<AllocationSiteWithWeakNext>(site)->set_weak_next(
2308  Cast<UnionOf<Undefined, AllocationSiteWithWeakNext>>(
2309  isolate()->heap()->allocation_sites_list()));
2310  isolate()->heap()->set_allocation_sites_list(
2311  *Cast<AllocationSiteWithWeakNext>(site));
2312  }
2313  return site;
2314 }

2316 template <typename MetaMapProviderFunc>
2317 Handle<Map> Factory::NewMapImpl(MetaMapProviderFunc&& meta_map_provider,
2318  InstanceType type, int instance_size,
2319  ElementsKind elements_kind,
2320  int inobject_properties,
2321  AllocationType allocation_type) {
2322  static_assert(LAST_JS_OBJECT_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
2323  DCHECK(!InstanceTypeChecker::MayHaveMapCheckFastCase(type));
2324  DCHECK_IMPLIES(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(type) &&
2325  !Map::CanHaveFastTransitionableElementsKind(type),
2326  IsDictionaryElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
2327  IsTerminalElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
2328  IsSharedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind));
2329  DCHECK(allocation_type == AllocationType::kMap ||
2330  allocation_type == AllocationType::kSharedMap);
2331  Tagged<HeapObject> result =
2332  allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(
2333  Map::kSize, allocation_type);
2334  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2335  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
2336  result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), meta_map_provider());
2337 
2338 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2339  CHECK_IMPLIES(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(type),
2340  V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(result.ptr()) >
2341  InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit);
2342 #endif
2343  isolate()->counters()->maps_created()->Increment();
2344  return handle(InitializeMap(Cast<Map>(result), type, instance_size,
2345  elements_kind, inobject_properties, roots),
2346  isolate());
2347 }
2348 
2349 Tagged<Map> Factory::InitializeMap(Tagged<Map> map, InstanceType type,
2350  int instance_size,
2351  ElementsKind elements_kind,
2352  int inobject_properties,
2353  ReadOnlyRoots roots) {
2354  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2355  map->set_bit_field(0);
2356  map->set_bit_field2(Map::Bits2::NewTargetIsBaseBit::encode(true));
2357  int bit_field3 =
2358  Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::encode(kInvalidEnumCacheSentinel) |
2359  Map::Bits3::OwnsDescriptorsBit::encode(true) |
2360  Map::Bits3::ConstructionCounterBits::encode(Map::kNoSlackTracking) |
2361  Map::Bits3::IsExtensibleBit::encode(true);
2362  map->set_bit_field3(bit_field3);
2363  map->set_instance_type(type);
2364  map->init_prototype_and_constructor_or_back_pointer(roots);
2365  map->set_instance_size(instance_size);
2366  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(type)) {
2367  // JSObjects that may be allocated in RO space must have RO maps.
2368  DCHECK_IMPLIES(InstanceTypeChecker::IsMaybeReadOnlyJSObject(type),
2369  ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(map));
2370  // Shared space JS objects have fixed layout and can have RO maps. No other
2371  // JS objects have RO maps.
2372  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!IsMaybeReadOnlyJSObjectMap(*map) &&
2373  !IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObjectMap(*map),
2374  !ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(map));
2375  map->SetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords(instance_size / kTaggedSize -
2376  inobject_properties);
2377  DCHECK_EQ(map->GetInObjectProperties(), inobject_properties);
2378  map->set_prototype_validity_cell(roots.invalid_prototype_validity_cell(),
2379  kRelaxedStore);
2380  } else {
2381  DCHECK_EQ(inobject_properties, 0);
2382  map->set_inobject_properties_start_or_constructor_function_index(0);
2383  map->set_prototype_validity_cell(Map::kPrototypeChainValidSmi,
2384  kRelaxedStore, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2385  }
2386  map->set_dependent_code(DependentCode::empty_dependent_code(roots),
2387  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2388  map->set_raw_transitions(Smi::zero(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2389  map->SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(inobject_properties);
2390  map->SetInstanceDescriptors(isolate(), roots.empty_descriptor_array(), 0,
2391  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2392  // Must be called only after |instance_type| and |instance_size| are set.
2393  map->set_visitor_id(Map::GetVisitorId(map));
2394  DCHECK(!map->is_in_retained_map_list());
2395  map->clear_padding();
2396  map->set_elements_kind(elements_kind);
2397  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.log_maps)) {
2398  LOG(isolate(), MapCreate(map));
2399  }
2400  return map;
2401 }
2402 
2403 Handle<Map> Factory::NewMap(DirectHandle<HeapObject> meta_map_holder,
2404  InstanceType type, int instance_size,
2405  ElementsKind elements_kind, int inobject_properties,
2406  AllocationType allocation_type) {
2407  auto meta_map_provider = [meta_map_holder] {
2408  // Tie new map to the same native context as given |meta_map_holder| object.
2409  Tagged<Map> meta_map = meta_map_holder->map();
2410  DCHECK(IsMapMap(meta_map));
2411  return meta_map;
2412  };
2413  Handle<Map> map =
2414  NewMapImpl(meta_map_provider, type, instance_size, elements_kind,
2415  inobject_properties, allocation_type);
2416  return map;
2417 }

2507 Handle<JSObject> Factory::CopyJSObject(DirectHandle<JSObject> source) {
2508  return CopyJSObjectWithAllocationSite(source, DirectHandle<AllocationSite>());
2509 }
2510 
2511 Handle<JSObject> Factory::CopyJSObjectWithAllocationSite(
2512  DirectHandle<JSObject> source, DirectHandle<AllocationSite> site) {
2513  DirectHandle<Map> map(source->map(), isolate());
2514 
2515  // We can only clone regexps, normal objects, api objects, errors or arrays.
2516  // Copying anything else will break invariants.
2517  InstanceType instance_type = map->instance_type();
2518  bool is_clonable_js_type =
2519  instance_type == JS_REG_EXP_TYPE || instance_type == JS_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2520  instance_type == JS_ERROR_TYPE || instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE ||
2521  instance_type == JS_SPECIAL_API_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2522  InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(instance_type);
2523  bool is_clonable_wasm_type = false;
2524 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2525  is_clonable_wasm_type = instance_type == WASM_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2526  instance_type == WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2527  instance_type == WASM_MEMORY_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2528  instance_type == WASM_MODULE_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2529  instance_type == WASM_TABLE_OBJECT_TYPE;
2530 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2531  CHECK(is_clonable_js_type || is_clonable_wasm_type);
2532 
2533  DCHECK(site.is_null() || AllocationSite::CanTrack(instance_type));
2534 
2535  int object_size = map->instance_size();
2536  int aligned_object_size = ALIGN_TO_ALLOCATION_ALIGNMENT(object_size);
2537  int adjusted_object_size = aligned_object_size;
2538  if (!site.is_null()) {
2539  DCHECK(V8_ALLOCATION_SITE_TRACKING_BOOL);
2540  adjusted_object_size +=
2541  ALIGN_TO_ALLOCATION_ALIGNMENT(sizeof(AllocationMemento));
2542  }
2543  Tagged<HeapObject> raw_clone =
2544  allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(
2545  adjusted_object_size, AllocationType::kYoung);
2546 
2547  DCHECK_NEWLY_ALLOCATED_OBJECT_IS_YOUNG(isolate(), raw_clone);
2548 
2549  Heap::CopyBlock(raw_clone.address(), source->address(), object_size);
2550  Handle<JSObject> clone(Cast<JSObject>(raw_clone), isolate());
2551 
2552  if (v8_flags.enable_unconditional_write_barriers) {
2553  // By default, we shouldn't need to update the write barrier here, as the
2554  // clone will be allocated in new space.
2555  const ObjectSlot start(raw_clone.address());
2556  const ObjectSlot end(raw_clone.address() + object_size);
2557  WriteBarrier::ForRange(isolate()->heap(), raw_clone, start, end);
2558  }
2559  if (!site.is_null()) {
2560  Tagged<AllocationMemento> alloc_memento = UncheckedCast<AllocationMemento>(
2561  Tagged<Object>(raw_clone.ptr() + aligned_object_size));
2562  InitializeAllocationMemento(alloc_memento, *site);
2563  }
2564 
2565  SLOW_DCHECK(clone->GetElementsKind() == source->GetElementsKind());
2566  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements = source->elements();
2567  // Update elements if necessary.
2568  if (elements->length() > 0) {
2569  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elem;
2570  if (elements->map() == *fixed_cow_array_map()) {
2571  elem = elements;
2572  } else if (source->HasDoubleElements()) {
2573  elem = *CopyFixedDoubleArray(
2574  handle(Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(elements), isolate()));
2575  } else {
2576  elem = *CopyFixedArray(handle(Cast<FixedArray>(elements), isolate()));
2577  }
2578  clone->set_elements(elem);
2579  }
2580 
2581  // Update properties if necessary.
2582  if (source->HasFastProperties()) {
2583  Tagged<PropertyArray> properties = source->property_array();
2584  if (properties->length() > 0) {
2585  // TODO(gsathya): Do not copy hash code.
2586  DirectHandle<PropertyArray> prop =
2587  CopyArrayWithMap(direct_handle(properties, isolate()),
2588  direct_handle(properties->map(), isolate()));
2589  clone->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*prop, kRelaxedStore);
2590  }
2591  } else {
2592  DirectHandle<Object> copied_properties;
2593  if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
2594  copied_properties = SwissNameDictionary::ShallowCopy(
2595  isolate(),
2596  direct_handle(source->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate()));
2597  } else {
2598  copied_properties =
2599  CopyFixedArray(handle(source->property_dictionary(), isolate()));
2600  }
2601  clone->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*copied_properties, kRelaxedStore);
2602  }
2603  return clone;
2604 }

2618  Tagged<Object> initial_value) {
