2626 template <typename T>
2627 Handle<T> Factory::CopyArrayWithMap(DirectHandle<T> src, DirectHandle<Map> map,
2628  AllocationType allocation) {
2629  int len = src->length();
2630  Tagged<HeapObject> new_object = AllocateRawFixedArray(len, allocation);
2631  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2632  new_object->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2633  Tagged<T> result = Cast<T>(new_object);
2634  initialize_length(result, len);
2635  // Copy the content.
2636  WriteBarrierMode mode = result->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
2637  T::CopyElements(isolate(), result, 0, *src, 0, len, mode);
2638  return handle(result, isolate());
2639 }
2640 
2641 template <typename T>
2642 Handle<T> Factory::CopyArrayAndGrow(DirectHandle<T> src, int grow_by,
2643  AllocationType allocation) {
2644  DCHECK_LT(0, grow_by);
2645  DCHECK_LE(grow_by, kMaxInt - src->length());
2646  int old_len = src->length();
2647  int new_len = old_len + grow_by;
2648  // TODO(jgruber,v8:14345): Use T::Allocate instead.
2649  Tagged<HeapObject> new_object = AllocateRawFixedArray(new_len, allocation);
2650  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2651  new_object->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), src->map(),
2652  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2653  Tagged<T> result = Cast<T>(new_object);
2654  initialize_length(result, new_len);
2655  // Copy the content.
2656  WriteBarrierMode mode = result->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
2657  T::CopyElements(isolate(), result, 0, *src, 0, old_len, mode);
2658  // TODO(jgruber,v8:14345): Enable the static assert once all T's support it:
2659  // static_assert(T::kElementSize == kTaggedSize);
2660  MemsetTagged(ObjectSlot(result->RawFieldOfElementAt(old_len)),
2661  read_only_roots().undefined_value(), grow_by);
2662  return handle(result, isolate());
2663 }

2713 Handle<WeakArrayList> Factory::CopyWeakArrayListAndGrow(
2714  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> src, int grow_by, AllocationType allocation) {
2715  int old_capacity = src->capacity();
2716  int new_capacity = old_capacity + grow_by;
2717  DCHECK_GE(new_capacity, old_capacity);
2718  Handle<WeakArrayList> result =
2719  NewUninitializedWeakArrayList(new_capacity, allocation);
2720  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2721  Tagged<WeakArrayList> raw = *result;
2722  int old_len = src->length();
2723  raw->set_length(old_len);
2724  // Copy the content.
2725  WriteBarrierMode mode = raw->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
2726  raw->CopyElements(isolate(), 0, *src, 0, old_len, mode);
2727  MemsetTagged(ObjectSlot(raw->data_start() + old_len),
2728  read_only_roots().undefined_value(), new_capacity - old_len);
2729  return result;
2730 }
2731 
2732 DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> Factory::CompactWeakArrayList(
2733  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> src, int new_capacity,
2734  AllocationType allocation) {
2735  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> result =
2736  NewUninitializedWeakArrayList(new_capacity, allocation);
2737 
2738  // Copy the content.
2739  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2740  Tagged<WeakArrayList> raw_src = *src;
2741  Tagged<WeakArrayList> raw_result = *result;
2742  WriteBarrierMode mode = raw_result->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
2743  int copy_to = 0, length = raw_src->length();
2744  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2745  Tagged<MaybeObject> element = raw_src->Get(i);
2746  if (element.IsCleared()) continue;
2747  raw_result->Set(copy_to++, element, mode);
2748  }
2749  raw_result->set_length(copy_to);
2750 
2751  MemsetTagged(ObjectSlot(raw_result->data_start() + copy_to),
2752  read_only_roots().undefined_value(), new_capacity - copy_to);
2753  return result;
2754 }

2885 DirectHandle<JSObject> Factory::NewFunctionPrototype(
2886  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
2887  // Make sure to use globals from the function's context, since the function
2888  // can be from a different context.
2889  DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context(function->native_context(),
2890  isolate());
2891  DirectHandle<Map> new_map;
2892  if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function->shared()->kind()))) {
2893  new_map = direct_handle(
2894  native_context->async_generator_object_prototype_map(), isolate());
2895  } else if (IsResumableFunction(function->shared()->kind())) {
2896  // Generator and async function prototypes can share maps since they
2897  // don't have "constructor" properties.
2898  new_map = direct_handle(native_context->generator_object_prototype_map(),
2899  isolate());
2900  } else {
2901  // Each function prototype gets a fresh map to avoid unwanted sharing of
2902  // maps between prototypes of different constructors.
2903  DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_function(native_context->object_function(),
2904  isolate());
2905  DCHECK(object_function->has_initial_map());
2906  new_map = direct_handle(object_function->initial_map(), isolate());
2907  }
2908 
2909  DCHECK(!new_map->is_prototype_map());
2910  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype = NewJSObjectFromMap(new_map);
2911 
2912  if (!IsResumableFunction(function->shared()->kind())) {
2913  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), prototype, constructor_string(), function,
2914  DONT_ENUM);
2915  }
2916 
2917  return prototype;
2918 }

2937 DirectHandle<Code> Factory::NewCodeObjectForEmbeddedBuiltin(
2938  DirectHandle<Code> code, Address off_heap_entry) {
2939  CHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate()->embedded_blob_code());
2940  CHECK_NE(0, isolate()->embedded_blob_code_size());
2941  CHECK(Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
2942 
2943  DCHECK(code->has_instruction_stream()); // Just generated as on-heap code.
2944  DCHECK(Builtins::IsBuiltinId(code->builtin_id()));
2945  DCHECK_EQ(code->inlined_bytecode_size(), 0);
2946  DCHECK_EQ(code->osr_offset(), BytecodeOffset::None());
2947  DCHECK_EQ(code->raw_deoptimization_data_or_interpreter_data(), Smi::zero());
2948  // .. because we don't explicitly initialize these flags:
2949  DCHECK(!code->marked_for_deoptimization());
2950  DCHECK(!code->can_have_weak_objects());
2951  DCHECK(!code->embedded_objects_cleared());
2952  // This check would fail. We explicitly clear any existing position tables
2953  // below. Note this isn't strictly necessary - we could keep the position
2954  // tables if we'd properly allocate them into RO space when needed.
2955  // DCHECK_EQ(code->raw_position_table(), *empty_byte_array());
2956 
2957  NewCodeOptions new_code_options = {
2958  code->kind(),
2959  code->builtin_id(),
2960  code->is_context_specialized(),
2961  code->is_turbofanned(),
2962  code->parameter_count(),
2963  code->instruction_size(),
2964  code->metadata_size(),
2965  code->inlined_bytecode_size(),
2966  code->osr_offset(),
2967  code->handler_table_offset(),
2968  code->constant_pool_offset(),
2969  code->code_comments_offset(),
2970  code->jump_table_info_offset(),
2971  code->unwinding_info_offset(),
2972  MaybeHandle<TrustedObject>{},
2973  MaybeHandle<DeoptimizationData>{},
2974  /*bytecode_offset_table=*/MaybeHandle<TrustedByteArray>{},
2975  /*source_position_table=*/MaybeHandle<TrustedByteArray>{},
2976  MaybeHandle<InstructionStream>{},
2977  off_heap_entry,
2978  };
2979 
2980  Handle<Code> new_code = NewCode(new_code_options);
2981 #if V8_ENABLE_GEARBOX
2982  if (Builtins::IsGearboxPlaceholder(new_code->builtin_id())) {
2983  new_code->set_is_gearbox_placeholder_builtin(true);
2984  }
2985 #endif // V8_ENABLE_GEARBOX
2986  return new_code;
2987 }

2989 DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> Factory::CopyBytecodeArray(
2990  DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> source) {
2991  DirectHandle<BytecodeWrapper> wrapper = NewBytecodeWrapper();
2992  int size = BytecodeArray::SizeFor(source->length());
2993  Tagged<BytecodeArray> copy = Cast<BytecodeArray>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
2994  size, AllocationType::kTrusted, *bytecode_array_map()));
2995  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2996  Tagged<BytecodeArray> raw_source = *source;
2997  copy->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());
2998  copy->set_length(raw_source->length());
2999  copy->set_frame_size(raw_source->frame_size());
3000  copy->set_parameter_count(raw_source->parameter_count());
3001  copy->set_max_arguments(raw_source->max_arguments());
3002  copy->set_incoming_new_target_or_generator_register(
3003  raw_source->incoming_new_target_or_generator_register());
3004  copy->set_constant_pool(raw_source->constant_pool());
3005  copy->set_handler_table(raw_source->handler_table());
3006  copy->set_wrapper(*wrapper);
3007  if (raw_source->has_source_position_table(kAcquireLoad)) {
3008  copy->set_source_position_table(
3009  raw_source->source_position_table(kAcquireLoad), kReleaseStore);
3010  } else {
3011  copy->clear_source_position_table(kReleaseStore);
3012  }
3013  raw_source->CopyBytecodesTo(copy);
3014  wrapper->set_bytecode(copy);
3015  return direct_handle(copy, isolate());
3016 }

3045 Handle<JSGlobalObject> Factory::NewJSGlobalObject(
3046  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor) {
3047  DCHECK(constructor->has_initial_map());
3048  DirectHandle<Map> map(constructor->initial_map(), isolate());
3049  DCHECK(map->is_dictionary_map());
3050 
3051  // Make sure no field properties are described in the initial map.
3052  // This guarantees us that normalizing the properties does not
3053  // require us to change property values to PropertyCells.
3054  DCHECK_EQ(map->NextFreePropertyIndex(), 0);
3055 
3056  // Make sure we don't have a ton of pre-allocated slots in the
3057  // global objects. They will be unused once we normalize the object.
3058  DCHECK_EQ(map->UnusedPropertyFields(), 0);
3059  DCHECK_EQ(map->GetInObjectProperties(), 0);
3060 
3061  // Initial size of the backing store to avoid resize of the storage during
3062  // bootstrapping. The size differs between the JS global object ad the
3063  // builtins object.
3064  int initial_size = 64;
3065 
3066  // Allocate a dictionary object for backing storage.
3067  int at_least_space_for = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() * 2 + initial_size;
3068  Handle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary =
3069  GlobalDictionary::New(isolate(), at_least_space_for);
3070 
3071  // The global object might be created from an object template with accessors.
3072  // Fill these accessors into the dictionary.
3073  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descs(map->instance_descriptors(isolate()),
3074  isolate());
3075  for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3076  PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
3077  // Only accessors are expected.
3078  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
3079  PropertyDetails d(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.attributes(),
3080  PropertyCellType::kMutable);
3081  DirectHandle<Name> name(descs->GetKey(i), isolate());
3082  DirectHandle<Object> value(descs->GetStrongValue(i), isolate());
3083  DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell = NewPropertyCell(name, d, value);
3084  // |dictionary| already contains enough space for all properties.
3085  USE(GlobalDictionary::Add(isolate(), dictionary, name, cell, d));
3086  }
3087 
3088  // Allocate the global object and initialize it with the backing store.
3089  Handle<JSGlobalObject> global(
3090  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(New(map, AllocationType::kOld)), isolate());
3091  InitializeJSObjectFromMap(*global, *dictionary, *map,
3092  NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper);
3093 
3094  // Create a new map for the global object.
3095  DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::CopyDropDescriptors(isolate(), map);
3096  Tagged<Map> raw_map = *new_map;
3097  raw_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
3098  raw_map->set_is_dictionary_map(true);
3099  LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(raw_map));
3100 
3101  // Set up the global object as a normalized object.
3102  global->set_global_dictionary(*dictionary, kReleaseStore);
3103  global->set_map(isolate(), raw_map, kReleaseStore);
3104 
3105  // Make sure result is a global object with properties in dictionary.
3106  DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*global) && !global->HasFastProperties());
3107  return global;
3108 }
3109 
3110 void Factory::InitializeJSObjectFromMap(Tagged<JSObject> obj,
3111  Tagged<Object> properties,
3112  Tagged<Map> map,
3113  NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
3114  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3115  obj->set_raw_properties_or_hash(properties, kRelaxedStore);
3116  obj->initialize_elements();
3117  // TODO(1240798): Initialize the object's body using valid initial values
3118  // according to the object's initial map. For example, if the map's
3119  // instance type is JS_ARRAY_TYPE, the length field should be initialized
3120  // to a number (e.g. Smi::zero()) and the elements initialized to a
3121  // fixed array (e.g. Heap::empty_fixed_array()). Currently, the object
3122  // verification code has to cope with (temporarily) invalid objects. See
3123  // for example, JSArray::JSArrayVerify).
3124  DCHECK_EQ(IsJSApiWrapperObjectMap(map),
3125  new_js_object_type == NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper);
3126  InitializeJSObjectBody(obj, map,
3127  new_js_object_type == NewJSObjectType::kNoAPIWrapper
3128  ? JSObject::kHeaderSize
3129  : JSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlots::kHeaderSize);
3130  if (new_js_object_type == NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper) {
3131  CppHeapObjectWrapper(obj).InitializeCppHeapWrapper();
3132  }
3133 }
3134 
3135 void Factory::InitializeJSObjectBody(Tagged<JSObject> obj, Tagged<Map> map,
3136  int start_offset) {
3137  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3138  if (start_offset == map->instance_size()) return;
3139  DCHECK_LT(start_offset, map->instance_size());
3140 
3141  // We cannot always fill with one_pointer_filler_map because objects
3142  // created from API functions expect their embedder fields to be initialized
3143  // with undefined_value.
3144  // Pre-allocated fields need to be initialized with undefined_value as well
3145  // so that object accesses before the constructor completes (e.g. in the
3146  // debugger) will not cause a crash.
3147 
3148  // In case of Array subclassing the |map| could already be transitioned
3149  // to different elements kind from the initial map on which we track slack.
3150  bool in_progress = map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress();
3151  obj->InitializeBody(map, start_offset, in_progress,
3152  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate()).one_pointer_filler_map_word(),
3153  *undefined_value());
3154  if (in_progress) {
3155  map->FindRootMap(isolate())->InobjectSlackTrackingStep(isolate());
3156  }
3157 }
3158 
3159 Handle<JSObject> Factory::NewJSObjectFromMap(
3160  DirectHandle<Map> map, AllocationType allocation,
3161  DirectHandle<AllocationSite> allocation_site,
3162  NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
3163  // JSFunctions should be allocated using AllocateFunction to be
3164  // properly initialized.
3165  DCHECK(!InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(*map));
3166 
3167  // Both types of global objects should be allocated using
3168  // AllocateGlobalObject to be properly initialized.
3169  DCHECK_NE(map->instance_type(), JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE);
3170 
3171  Tagged<JSObject> js_obj = Cast<JSObject>(
3172  AllocateRawWithAllocationSite(map, allocation, allocation_site));
3173 
3174  InitializeJSObjectFromMap(js_obj, *empty_fixed_array(), *map,
3175  new_js_object_type);
3176 
3177  DCHECK(js_obj->HasFastElements() ||
3178  (isolate()->bootstrapper()->IsActive() ||
3179  *map == isolate()
3180  ->raw_native_context()
3181  ->js_array_template_literal_object_map()) ||
3182  js_obj->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements() ||
3183  js_obj->HasFastStringWrapperElements() ||
3184  js_obj->HasFastArgumentsElements() ||
3185  js_obj->HasDictionaryElements() || js_obj->HasSharedArrayElements());
3186  return handle(js_obj, isolate());
3187 }

3189 Handle<JSObject> Factory::NewSlowJSObjectFromMap(
3190  DirectHandle<Map> map, int capacity, AllocationType allocation,
3191  DirectHandle<AllocationSite> allocation_site,
3192  NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
3193  DCHECK(map->is_dictionary_map());
3194  DirectHandle<HeapObject> object_properties;
3195  if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3196  object_properties = NewSwissNameDictionary(capacity, allocation);
3197  } else {
3198  object_properties = NameDictionary::New(isolate(), capacity);
3199  }
3200  Handle<JSObject> js_object =
3201  NewJSObjectFromMap(map, allocation, allocation_site, new_js_object_type);
3202  js_object->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*object_properties, kRelaxedStore);
3203  return js_object;
3204 }

3210 DirectHandle<JSObject> Factory::NewSlowJSObjectWithPropertiesAndElements(
3211  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> prototype, DirectHandle<HeapObject> properties,
3212  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements) {
3213  DCHECK(IsPropertyDictionary(*properties));
3214 
3215  DirectHandle<Map> object_map =
3216  isolate()->slow_object_with_object_prototype_map();
3217  if (object_map->prototype() != *prototype) {
3218  object_map = Map::TransitionRootMapToPrototypeForNewObject(
3219  isolate(), object_map, prototype);
3220  }
3221  DCHECK(object_map->is_dictionary_map());
3222  DirectHandle<JSObject> object =
3223  NewJSObjectFromMap(object_map, AllocationType::kYoung);
3224  object->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*properties);
3225  if (*elements != read_only_roots().empty_fixed_array()) {
3226  DCHECK(IsNumberDictionary(*elements));
3227  object_map = JSObject::GetElementsTransitionMap(isolate(), object,
3228  DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS);
3229  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate(), object, object_map);
3230  object->set_elements(*elements);
3231  }
3232  return object;
3233 }

3235 Handle<JSArray> Factory::NewJSArray(ElementsKind elements_kind, int length,
3236  int capacity,
3237  ArrayStorageAllocationMode mode,
3238  AllocationType allocation) {
3239  DCHECK(capacity >= length);

3242  allocation);
3243  }

3249  elms, elements_kind, length, allocation));
3250 }

3263 Handle<JSArray> Factory::NewJSArrayWithUnverifiedElements(

3314 void Factory::NewJSArrayStorage(DirectHandle<JSArray> array, int length,
3315  int capacity, ArrayStorageAllocationMode mode) {
3316  DCHECK(capacity >= length);
3317 
3318  if (capacity == 0) {
3319  Tagged<JSArray> raw = *array;
3320  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3321  raw->set_length(Smi::zero());
3322  raw->set_elements(*empty_fixed_array());
3323  return;
3324  }
3325 
3326  HandleScope inner_scope(isolate());
3327  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elms =
3328  NewJSArrayStorage(array->GetElementsKind(), capacity, mode);
3329  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3330  Tagged<JSArray> raw = *array;
3331  raw->set_elements(*elms);
3332  raw->set_length(Smi::FromInt(length));
3333 }

3335 DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> Factory::NewJSArrayStorage(
3336  ElementsKind elements_kind, int capacity, ArrayStorageAllocationMode mode) {
3337  DCHECK_GT(capacity, 0);
3338  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elms;
3339  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3340  if (mode == ArrayStorageAllocationMode::DONT_INITIALIZE_ARRAY_ELEMENTS) {
3341  elms = NewFixedDoubleArray(capacity);
3342  } else {
3343  DCHECK_EQ(
3344  mode,
3345  ArrayStorageAllocationMode::INITIALIZE_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_WITH_HOLE);
3346  elms = NewFixedDoubleArrayWithHoles(capacity);
3347  }
3348  } else {
3349  DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind));
3350  if (mode == ArrayStorageAllocationMode::DONT_INITIALIZE_ARRAY_ELEMENTS) {
3351  elms = NewFixedArray(capacity);
3352  } else {
3353  DCHECK_EQ(
3354  mode,
3355  ArrayStorageAllocationMode::INITIALIZE_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_WITH_HOLE);
3356  elms = NewFixedArrayWithHoles(capacity);
3357  }
3358  }
3359  return elms;
3360 }

3389 DirectHandle<JSWrappedFunction> Factory::NewJSWrappedFunction(
3390  DirectHandle<NativeContext> creation_context, DirectHandle<Object> target) {
3391  DCHECK(IsCallable(*target));
3392  DirectHandle<Map> map(Cast<Map>(creation_context->GetNoCell(
3393  Context::WRAPPED_FUNCTION_MAP_INDEX)),
3394  isolate());
3395  // 2. Let wrapped be ! MakeBasicObject(internalSlotsList).
3396  // 3. Set wrapped.[[Prototype]] to
3397  // callerRealm.[[Intrinsics]].[[%Function->prototype%]].
3398  // 4. Set wrapped.[[Call]] as described in 2.1.
3399  DirectHandle<JSWrappedFunction> wrapped =
3400  Cast<JSWrappedFunction>(isolate()->factory()->NewJSObjectFromMap(map));
3401  // 5. Set wrapped.[[WrappedTargetFunction]] to Target.
3402  wrapped->set_wrapped_target_function(Cast<JSCallable>(*target));
3403  // 6. Set wrapped.[[Realm]] to callerRealm.
3404  wrapped->set_context(*creation_context);
3405  // TODO(v8:11989): https://github.com/tc39/proposal-shadowrealm/pull/348
3406 
3407  return wrapped;
3408 }

3539 
3540 MaybeHandle<JSArrayBuffer> Factory::NewJSArrayBufferAndBackingStore(
3541  size_t byte_length, size_t max_byte_length, InitializedFlag initialized,
3542  ResizableFlag resizable, AllocationType allocation) {
3543  DCHECK_LE(byte_length, max_byte_length);
3544  std::unique_ptr<BackingStore> backing_store = nullptr;
3545 
3546  if (resizable == ResizableFlag::kResizable) {
3547  size_t page_size, initial_pages, max_pages;
3548  if (JSArrayBuffer::GetResizableBackingStorePageConfiguration(
3549  isolate(), byte_length, max_byte_length, kDontThrow, &page_size,
3550  &initial_pages, &max_pages)
3551  .IsNothing()) {
3552  return MaybeHandle<JSArrayBuffer>();
3553  }
3554 
3555  backing_store = BackingStore::TryAllocateAndPartiallyCommitMemory(
3556  isolate(), byte_length, max_byte_length, page_size, initial_pages,
3557  max_pages, WasmMemoryFlag::kNotWasm, SharedFlag::kNotShared);
3558  if (!backing_store) return MaybeHandle<JSArrayBuffer>();
3559  } else {
3560  if (byte_length > 0) {
3561  backing_store = BackingStore::Allocate(
3562  isolate(), byte_length, SharedFlag::kNotShared, initialized);
3563  if (!backing_store) return MaybeHandle<JSArrayBuffer>();
3564  }
3565  }
3566  DirectHandle<Map> map(
3567  isolate()->native_context()->array_buffer_fun()->initial_map(),
3568  isolate());
3569  auto array_buffer = Cast<JSArrayBuffer>(
3570  NewJSObjectFromMap(map, allocation, DirectHandle<AllocationSite>::null(),
3571  NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper));
3572  array_buffer->Setup(SharedFlag::kNotShared, resizable,
3573  std::move(backing_store), isolate());
3574  return array_buffer;
3575 }

3577 Handle<JSArrayBuffer> Factory::NewJSSharedArrayBuffer(

3587  : ResizableFlag::kNotResizable;
3588  result->Setup(SharedFlag::kShared, resizable, std::move(backing_store),
3589  isolate());

3634 void Factory::TypeAndSizeForElementsKind(ElementsKind kind,
3635  ExternalArrayType* array_type,
3636  size_t* element_size) {
3637  switch (kind) {
3638 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
3639  case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: \
3640  *array_type = kExternal##Type##Array; \
3641  *element_size = sizeof(ctype); \
3642  break;
3643  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
3644  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS_WITH_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
3645 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
3646 
3647  default:
3648  UNREACHABLE();
3649  }
3650 }

3652 Handle<JSArrayBufferView> Factory::NewJSArrayBufferView(
3653  DirectHandle<Map> map, DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elements,
3654  DirectHandle<JSArrayBuffer> buffer, size_t byte_offset,
3655  size_t byte_length) {
3656  if (!IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(map->elements_kind())) {
3657  CHECK_LE(byte_length, buffer->GetByteLength());
3658  CHECK_LE(byte_offset, buffer->GetByteLength());
3659  CHECK_LE(byte_offset + byte_length, buffer->GetByteLength());
3660  }
3661 
3662  Handle<JSArrayBufferView> array_buffer_view =
3663  Cast<JSArrayBufferView>(NewJSObjectFromMap(
3664  map, AllocationType::kYoung, DirectHandle<AllocationSite>::null(),
3665  NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper));
3666  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3667  Tagged<JSArrayBufferView> raw = *array_buffer_view;
3668  raw->set_elements(*elements, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3669  raw->set_buffer(*buffer, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3670  raw->set_byte_offset(byte_offset);
3671  raw->set_byte_length(byte_length);
3672  raw->set_bit_field(0);
3673  // TODO(v8) remove once embedder data slots are always zero-initialized.
3674  InitEmbedderFields(raw, Smi::zero());
3675  DCHECK_EQ(raw->GetEmbedderFieldCount(),
3676  v8::ArrayBufferView::kEmbedderFieldCount);
3677  return array_buffer_view;
3678 }
3679 
3680 Handle<JSTypedArray> Factory::NewJSTypedArray(
3681  ExternalArrayType type, DirectHandle<JSArrayBuffer> buffer,
3682  size_t byte_offset, size_t length, bool is_length_tracking) {
3683  size_t element_size;
3684  ElementsKind elements_kind;
3685  JSTypedArray::ForFixedTypedArray(type, &element_size, &elements_kind);
3686 
3687  const bool is_backed_by_rab =
3688  buffer->is_resizable_by_js() && !buffer->is_shared();
3689 
3690  DirectHandle<Map> map;
3691  if (is_backed_by_rab || is_length_tracking) {
3692  map = direct_handle(
3693  isolate()->raw_native_context()->TypedArrayElementsKindToRabGsabCtorMap(
3694  elements_kind),
3695  isolate());
3696  } else {
3697  map = direct_handle(
3698  isolate()->raw_native_context()->TypedArrayElementsKindToCtorMap(
3699  elements_kind),
3700  isolate());
3701  }
3702 
3703  if (is_length_tracking) {
3704  // Security: enforce the invariant that length-tracking TypedArrays have
3705  // their length and byte_length set to 0.
3706  length = 0;
3707  }
3708 
3709  CHECK_LE(length, JSTypedArray::kMaxByteLength / element_size);
3710  CHECK_EQ(0, byte_offset % element_size);
3711  size_t byte_length = length * element_size;
3712 
3713  Handle<JSTypedArray> typed_array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(NewJSArrayBufferView(
3714  map, empty_byte_array(), buffer, byte_offset, byte_length));
3715  Tagged<JSTypedArray> raw = *typed_array;
3716  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3717  raw->SetOffHeapDataPtr(isolate(), buffer->backing_store(), byte_offset);
3718  raw->set_is_length_tracking(is_length_tracking);
3719  raw->set_is_backed_by_rab(is_backed_by_rab);
3720  return typed_array;
3721 }
3722 
3723 Handle<JSDataViewOrRabGsabDataView> Factory::NewJSDataViewOrRabGsabDataView(
3724  DirectHandle<JSArrayBuffer> buffer, size_t byte_offset, size_t byte_length,
3725  bool is_length_tracking) {
3726  if (is_length_tracking) {
3727  // Security: enforce the invariant that length-tracking DataViews have their
3728  // byte_length set to 0.
3729  byte_length = 0;
3730  }
3731  bool is_backed_by_rab = !buffer->is_shared() && buffer->is_resizable_by_js();
3732  DirectHandle<Map> map;
3733  if (is_backed_by_rab || is_length_tracking) {
3734  map = direct_handle(
3735  isolate()->native_context()->js_rab_gsab_data_view_map(), isolate());
3736  } else {
3737  map = direct_handle(
3738  isolate()->native_context()->data_view_fun()->initial_map(), isolate());
3739  }
3740  Handle<JSDataViewOrRabGsabDataView> obj =
3741  Cast<JSDataViewOrRabGsabDataView>(NewJSArrayBufferView(
3742  map, empty_fixed_array(), buffer, byte_offset, byte_length));
3743  obj->set_data_pointer(
3744  isolate(), static_cast<uint8_t*>(buffer->backing_store()) + byte_offset);
3745  obj->set_is_length_tracking(is_length_tracking);
3746  obj->set_is_backed_by_rab(is_backed_by_rab);
3747  return obj;
3748 }

3751  DirectHandle<Number> read, DirectHandle<Number> written) {

3764 MaybeDirectHandle<JSBoundFunction> Factory::NewJSBoundFunction(
3765  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target_function, DirectHandle<JSAny> bound_this,
3766  base::Vector<DirectHandle<Object>> bound_args,
3767  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> prototype) {
3768  DCHECK(IsCallable(*target_function));
3769  static_assert(Code::kMaxArguments <= FixedArray::kMaxLength);
3770  if (bound_args.length() >= Code::kMaxArguments) {
3771  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate(),
3772  NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kTooManyArguments));
3773  }
3774 
3775  SaveAndSwitchContext save(isolate(),
3776  target_function->GetCreationContext().value());
3777 
3778  // Create the [[BoundArguments]] for the result.
3779  DirectHandle<FixedArray> bound_arguments;
3780  if (bound_args.empty()) {
3781  bound_arguments = empty_fixed_array();
3782  } else {
3783  bound_arguments = NewFixedArray(bound_args.length());
3784  for (int i = 0; i < bound_args.length(); ++i) {
3785  bound_arguments->set(i, *bound_args[i]);
3786  }
3787  }
3788 
3789  // Setup the map for the JSBoundFunction instance.
3790  DirectHandle<Map> map =
3791  IsConstructor(*target_function)
3792  ? isolate()->bound_function_with_constructor_map()
3793  : isolate()->bound_function_without_constructor_map();
3794  if (map->prototype() != *prototype) {
3795  map = Map::TransitionRootMapToPrototypeForNewObject(isolate(), map,
3796  prototype);
3797  }
3798  DCHECK_EQ(IsConstructor(*target_function), map->is_constructor());
3799 
3800  // Setup the JSBoundFunction instance.
3801  DirectHandle<JSBoundFunction> result =
3802  Cast<JSBoundFunction>(NewJSObjectFromMap(map, AllocationType::kYoung));
3803  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3804  Tagged<JSBoundFunction> raw = *result;
3805  raw->set_bound_target_function(Cast<JSCallable>(*target_function),
3806  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3807  raw->set_bound_this(*bound_this, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3808  raw->set_bound_arguments(*bound_arguments, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3809  return result;
3810 }

3812 // ES6 section 9.5.15 ProxyCreate (target, handler)
3813 Handle<JSProxy> Factory::NewJSProxy(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
3814  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler,
3815  bool revocable) {
3816  // Allocate the proxy object.
3817  DirectHandle<Map> map = IsCallable(*target)
3818  ? IsConstructor(*target)
3819  ? isolate()->proxy_constructor_map()
3820  : isolate()->proxy_callable_map()
3821  : isolate()->proxy_map();
3822  DCHECK(IsNull(map->prototype(), isolate()));
3823  Tagged<JSProxy> result = Cast<JSProxy>(New(map, AllocationType::kYoung));
3824  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3825  result->initialize_properties(isolate());
3826  result->set_target(*target, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3827  result->set_handler(*handler, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3828  result->set_flags(JSProxy::IsRevocableBit::encode(revocable));
3829  return handle(result, isolate());
3830 }

3832 Handle<JSGlobalProxy> Factory::NewUninitializedJSGlobalProxy(int size) {
3833  // Create an empty shell of a JSGlobalProxy that needs to be reinitialized
3834  // via ReinitializeJSGlobalProxy later.
3835  DirectHandle<Map> map = NewContextlessMap(JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE, size);
3836  // Maintain invariant expected from any JSGlobalProxy.
3837  {
3838  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3839  Tagged<Map> raw = *map;
3840  raw->set_is_access_check_needed(true);
3841  raw->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
3842  LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(raw));
3843  }
3844  Handle<JSGlobalProxy> proxy = Cast<JSGlobalProxy>(NewJSObjectFromMap(
3845  map, AllocationType::kOld, DirectHandle<AllocationSite>::null(),
3846  NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper));
3847  // Create identity hash early in case there is any JS collection containing
3848  // a global proxy key and needs to be rehashed after deserialization.
3849  proxy->GetOrCreateIdentityHash(isolate());
3850  return proxy;
3851 }
3852 
3853 void Factory::ReinitializeJSGlobalProxy(DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> object,
3854  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor) {
3855  DCHECK(constructor->has_initial_map());
3856  DirectHandle<Map> map(constructor->initial_map(), isolate());
3857  DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate());
3858 
3859  // The proxy's hash should be retained across reinitialization.
3860  DirectHandle<Object> raw_properties_or_hash(object->raw_properties_or_hash(),
3861  isolate());
3862 
3863  if (old_map->is_prototype_map()) {
3864  map = Map::Copy(isolate(), map, "CopyAsPrototypeForJSGlobalProxy");
3865  map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
3866  }
3867  JSObject::NotifyMapChange(old_map, map, isolate());
3868  old_map->NotifyLeafMapLayoutChange(isolate());
3869 
3870  // Check that the already allocated object has the same size and type as
3871  // objects allocated using the constructor.
3872  DCHECK(map->instance_size() == old_map->instance_size());
3873  DCHECK(map->instance_type() == old_map->instance_type());
3874 
3875  // In order to keep heap in consistent state there must be no allocations
3876  // before object re-initialization is finished.
3877  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3878 
3879  // Reset the map for the object.
3880  Tagged<JSGlobalProxy> raw = *object;
3881  raw->set_map(isolate(), *map, kReleaseStore);
3882 
3883  // Reinitialize the object from the constructor map.
3884  InitializeJSObjectFromMap(raw, *raw_properties_or_hash, *map,
3885  NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper);
3886  // Ensure that the object and constructor belongs to the same native context.
3887  DCHECK_EQ(object->map()->map(), constructor->map()->map());
3888 }

3890 Handle<JSMessageObject> Factory::NewJSMessageObject(
3891  MessageTemplate message, DirectHandle<Object> argument, int start_position,
3892  int end_position, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
3893  int bytecode_offset, DirectHandle<Script> script,
3894  DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace) {
3895  DirectHandle<Map> map = message_object_map();
3896  Tagged<JSMessageObject> message_obj =
3897  Cast<JSMessageObject>(New(map, AllocationType::kYoung));
3898  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3899  message_obj->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*empty_fixed_array(),
3900  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3901  message_obj->initialize_elements();
3902  message_obj->set_elements(*empty_fixed_array(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3903  message_obj->set_type(message);
3904  message_obj->set_argument(*argument, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3905  message_obj->set_start_position(start_position);
3906  message_obj->set_end_position(end_position);
3907  message_obj->set_script(*script, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3908  if (start_position >= 0) {
3909  // If there's a start_position, then there's no need to store the
3910  // SharedFunctionInfo as it will never be necessary to regenerate the
3911  // position.
3912  message_obj->set_shared_info(Smi::FromInt(-1));
3913  message_obj->set_bytecode_offset(Smi::FromInt(0));
3914  } else {
3915  message_obj->set_bytecode_offset(Smi::FromInt(bytecode_offset));
3916  if (shared_info.is_null()) {
3917  message_obj->set_shared_info(Smi::FromInt(-1));
3918  DCHECK_EQ(bytecode_offset, -1);
3919  } else {
3920  message_obj->set_shared_info(*shared_info, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3921  DCHECK_GE(bytecode_offset, kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset);
3922  }
3923  }
3924 
3925  if (stack_trace.is_null()) {
3926  message_obj->set_stack_trace(*the_hole_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3927  } else {
3928  message_obj->set_stack_trace(*stack_trace, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3929  }
3930  message_obj->set_error_level(v8::Isolate::kMessageError);
3931  return handle(message_obj, isolate());
3932 }

3963 Handle<String> Factory::SizeToString(size_t value, bool check_cache) {
3964  Handle<String> result;
3965  NumberCacheMode cache_mode =
3966  check_cache ? NumberCacheMode::kBoth : NumberCacheMode::kIgnore;
3967  if (value <= Smi::kMaxValue) {
3968  int32_t int32v = static_cast<int32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
3969  // SmiToString sets the hash when needed, we can return immediately.
3970  return SmiToString(Smi::FromInt(int32v), cache_mode);
3971  } else if (value <= kMaxSafeInteger) {
3972  double double_value = static_cast<double>(value);
3973  // The value is already out of Smi range, so canonicalization can't
3974  // succeed. Skip it.
3975  result = DoubleToString(double_value, false, cache_mode);
3976  } else {
3977  char arr[kNumberToStringBufferSize];
3978  base::Vector<char> buffer(arr, arraysize(arr));
3979  // Build the string backwards from the least significant digit.
3980  int i = buffer.length();
3981  size_t value_copy = value;
3982  buffer[--i] = '\0';
3983  do {
3984  buffer[--i] = '0' + (value_copy % 10);
3985  value_copy /= 10;
3986  } while (value_copy > 0);
3987  char* string = buffer.begin() + i;
3988  // No way to cache this; we'd need an {Object} to use as key.
3989  result = NewStringFromAsciiChecked(string);
3990  }
3991  {
3992  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3993  Tagged<String> raw = *result;
3994  if (value <= JSArray::kMaxArrayIndex &&
3995  raw->raw_hash_field() == String::kEmptyHashField) {
3996  uint32_t raw_hash_field = StringHasher::MakeArrayIndexHash(
3997  static_cast<uint32_t>(value), raw->length());
3998  raw->set_raw_hash_field(raw_hash_field);
3999  }
4000  }
4001  return result;
4002 }

4087 Handle<JSObject> Factory::NewArgumentsObject(DirectHandle<JSFunction> callee,
4088  int length) {
4089  bool strict_mode_callee = is_strict(callee->shared()->language_mode()) ||
4090  !callee->shared()->has_simple_parameters();
4091  DirectHandle<Map> map = strict_mode_callee
4092  ? isolate()->strict_arguments_map()
4093  : isolate()->sloppy_arguments_map();
4094  AllocationSiteUsageContext context(isolate(), Handle<AllocationSite>(),
4095  false);

4099  Object::SetProperty(isolate(), result, length_string(), value,
4100  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
4101  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
4102  .Assert();
4103  if (!strict_mode_callee) {
4104  Object::SetProperty(isolate(), result, callee_string(), callee,
4105  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
4106  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
4107  .Assert();
4108  }
4109  return result;
4110 }

4112 Handle<Map> Factory::ObjectLiteralMapFromCache(
4113  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context, int number_of_properties) {
4114  // Use initial slow object proto map for too many properties.
4115  if (number_of_properties >= JSObject::kMapCacheSize) {
4116  return handle(context->slow_object_with_object_prototype_map(), isolate());
4117  }
4118  // TODO(chromium:1503456): remove once fixed.
4119  CHECK_LE(0, number_of_properties);
4120 
4121  DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> cache(Cast<WeakFixedArray>(context->map_cache()),
4122  isolate());
4123 
4124  // Check to see whether there is a matching element in the cache.
4125  Tagged<MaybeObject> result = cache->get(number_of_properties);
4126  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
4127  if (result.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object)) {
4128  Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(heap_object);
4129  DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
4130  return handle(map, isolate());
4131  }
4132 
4133  // Create a new map and add it to the cache.
4134  Handle<Map> map = Map::Create(isolate(), number_of_properties);
4135  DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
4136  cache->set(number_of_properties, MakeWeak(*map));
4137  return map;
4138 }

4218 DirectHandle<RegExpData> Factory::NewAtomRegExpData(
4219  DirectHandle<String> source, JSRegExp::Flags flags,
4220  DirectHandle<String> pattern) {
4221  DirectHandle<RegExpDataWrapper> wrapper = NewRegExpDataWrapper();
4222  int size = AtomRegExpData::kSize;
4223  Tagged<HeapObject> result = AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
4224  size, AllocationType::kTrusted, read_only_roots().atom_regexp_data_map());
4225  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4226  Tagged<AtomRegExpData> instance = Cast<AtomRegExpData>(result);
4227  instance->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());
4228  instance->set_type_tag(RegExpData::Type::ATOM);
4229  instance->set_source(*source);
4230  instance->set_flags(flags);
4231  instance->set_pattern(*pattern);
4232  Tagged<RegExpDataWrapper> raw_wrapper = *wrapper;
4233  instance->set_wrapper(raw_wrapper);
4234  raw_wrapper->set_data(instance);
4235  return direct_handle(instance, isolate());
4236 }

4238 DirectHandle<RegExpData> Factory::NewIrRegExpData(DirectHandle<String> source,
4239  JSRegExp::Flags flags,
4240  int capture_count,
4241  uint32_t backtrack_limit) {
4242  DirectHandle<RegExpDataWrapper> wrapper = NewRegExpDataWrapper();
4243  int size = IrRegExpData::kSize;
4244  Tagged<HeapObject> result = AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
4245  size, AllocationType::kTrusted, read_only_roots().ir_regexp_data_map());
4246  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4247  Tagged<IrRegExpData> instance = Cast<IrRegExpData>(result);
4248  instance->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());
4249  instance->set_type_tag(RegExpData::Type::IRREGEXP);
4250  instance->set_source(*source);
4251  instance->set_flags(flags);
4252  instance->clear_latin1_code();
4253  instance->clear_uc16_code();
4254  instance->clear_latin1_bytecode();
4255  instance->clear_uc16_bytecode();
4256  instance->set_capture_name_map(Smi::FromInt(JSRegExp::kUninitializedValue));
4257  instance->set_max_register_count(JSRegExp::kUninitializedValue);
4258  instance->set_capture_count(capture_count);
4259  int ticks_until_tier_up = v8_flags.regexp_tier_up
4260  ? v8_flags.regexp_tier_up_ticks
4261  : JSRegExp::kUninitializedValue;
4262  instance->set_ticks_until_tier_up(ticks_until_tier_up);
4263  instance->set_backtrack_limit(backtrack_limit);
4264  Tagged<RegExpDataWrapper> raw_wrapper = *wrapper;
4265  instance->set_wrapper(raw_wrapper);
4266  raw_wrapper->set_data(instance);
4267  return direct_handle(instance, isolate());
4268 }

4270 DirectHandle<RegExpData> Factory::NewExperimentalRegExpData(
4271  DirectHandle<String> source, JSRegExp::Flags flags, int capture_count) {
4272  DirectHandle<RegExpDataWrapper> wrapper = NewRegExpDataWrapper();
4273  int size = IrRegExpData::kSize;
4274  Tagged<HeapObject> result = AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
4275  size, AllocationType::kTrusted, read_only_roots().ir_regexp_data_map());
4276  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4277  Tagged<IrRegExpData> instance = Cast<IrRegExpData>(result);
4278  // TODO(mbid,v8:10765): At the moment the ExperimentalRegExpData is just an
4279  // alias of IrRegExpData, with most fields set to some default/uninitialized
4280  // value. This is because EXPERIMENTAL and IRREGEXP regexps take the same code
4281  // path in `RegExpExecInternal`, which reads off various fields from this
4282  // struct. `RegExpExecInternal` should probably distinguish between
4283  // EXPERIMENTAL and IRREGEXP, and then we can get rid of all the IRREGEXP only
4284  // fields.
4285  instance->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());
4286  instance->set_type_tag(RegExpData::Type::EXPERIMENTAL);
4287  instance->set_source(*source);
4288  instance->set_flags(flags);
4289  instance->clear_latin1_code();
4290  instance->clear_uc16_code();
4291  instance->clear_latin1_bytecode();
4292  instance->clear_uc16_bytecode();
4293  instance->set_capture_name_map(Smi::FromInt(JSRegExp::kUninitializedValue));
4294  instance->set_max_register_count(JSRegExp::kUninitializedValue);
4295  instance->set_capture_count(capture_count);
4296  instance->set_ticks_until_tier_up(JSRegExp::kUninitializedValue);
4297  instance->set_backtrack_limit(JSRegExp::kUninitializedValue);
4298  Tagged<RegExpDataWrapper> raw_wrapper = *wrapper;
4299  instance->set_wrapper(raw_wrapper);
4300  raw_wrapper->set_data(instance);
4301  return direct_handle(instance, isolate());
4302 }

4304 DirectHandle<Object> Factory::GlobalConstantFor(DirectHandle<Name> name) {
4305  if (Name::Equals(isolate(), name, undefined_string())) {
4306  return undefined_value();
4307  }
4308  if (Name::Equals(isolate(), name, NaN_string())) return nan_value();
4309  if (Name::Equals(isolate(), name, Infinity_string())) return infinity_value();
4310  return Handle<Object>::null();
4311 }

4313 DirectHandle<String> Factory::ToPrimitiveHintString(ToPrimitiveHint hint) {
4314  switch (hint) {

4316  return default_string();
4317  case ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber:

4319  case ToPrimitiveHint::kString:
4320  return string_string();

4324 
4325 DirectHandle<Map> Factory::CreateSloppyFunctionMap(
4326  FunctionMode function_mode,
4327  MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction> maybe_empty_function) {
4328  // TODO(syg): Does sloppy/strict function map distinction need to exist
4329  // anymore after V8_FUNCTION_ARGUMENTS_CALLER_ARE_OWN_PROPS is removed?
4330  bool has_prototype = IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode);
4331  int header_size = has_prototype ? JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype
4332  : JSFunction::kSizeWithoutPrototype;
4333  int descriptors_count = has_prototype ? 3 : 2;
4334 #ifdef V8_FUNCTION_ARGUMENTS_CALLER_ARE_OWN_PROPS
4335  descriptors_count += 2;
4336 #endif
4337  int inobject_properties_count = 0;
4338  if (IsFunctionModeWithName(function_mode)) ++inobject_properties_count;
4339 
4340  DirectHandle<Map> map = NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4341  JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, header_size + inobject_properties_count * kTaggedSize,
4342  TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, inobject_properties_count);
4343  {
4344  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4345  Tagged<Map> raw_map = *map;
4346  raw_map->set_has_prototype_slot(has_prototype);
4347  raw_map->set_is_constructor(has_prototype);
4348  raw_map->set_is_callable(true);
4349  }
4350  DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function;
4351  if (maybe_empty_function.ToHandle(&empty_function)) {
4352  // Temporarily set constructor to empty function to calm down map verifier.
4353  map->SetConstructor(*empty_function);
4354  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, empty_function);
4355  } else {
4356  // |maybe_empty_function| is allowed to be empty only during empty function
4357  // creation.
4358  DCHECK(IsUndefined(isolate()->raw_native_context()->GetNoCell(
4359  Context::EMPTY_FUNCTION_INDEX)));
4360  }
4361 
4362  //
4363  // Setup descriptors array.
4364  //
4365  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, descriptors_count);
4366 
4367  PropertyAttributes ro_attribs =
4368  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY);
4369  PropertyAttributes rw_attribs =
4370  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE);
4371  PropertyAttributes roc_attribs =
4372  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY);
4373 
4374  int field_index = 0;
4375  static_assert(
4376  JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex == 0);
4377  { // Add length accessor.
4378  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4379  length_string(), function_length_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4380  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4381  }
4382 
4383  static_assert(
4384  JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex == 1);
4385  if (IsFunctionModeWithName(function_mode)) {
4386  // Add name field.
4387  DirectHandle<Name> name = isolate()->factory()->name_string();
4388  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), name, field_index++,
4389  roc_attribs, Representation::Tagged());
4390  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4391 
4392  } else {
4393  // Add name accessor.
4394  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4395  name_string(), function_name_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4396  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4397  }
4398 #ifdef V8_FUNCTION_ARGUMENTS_CALLER_ARE_OWN_PROPS
4399  { // Add arguments accessor.
4400  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4401  arguments_string(), function_arguments_accessor(), ro_attribs);
4402  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4403  }
4404  { // Add caller accessor.
4405  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4406  caller_string(), function_caller_accessor(), ro_attribs);
4407  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4408  }
4409 #endif // V8_FUNCTION_ARGUMENTS_CALLER_ARE_OWN_PROPS
4410  if (IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode)) {
4411  // Add prototype accessor.
4412  PropertyAttributes attribs =
4413  IsFunctionModeWithWritablePrototype(function_mode) ? rw_attribs
4414  : ro_attribs;
4415  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4416  prototype_string(), function_prototype_accessor(), attribs);
4417  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4418  }
4419  DCHECK_EQ(inobject_properties_count, field_index);
4420  DCHECK_EQ(
4421  0, map->instance_descriptors(isolate())->number_of_slack_descriptors());
4422  LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(*map));
4423  return map;
4424 }
4425 
4426 DirectHandle<Map> Factory::CreateStrictFunctionMap(
4427  FunctionMode function_mode, DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function) {
4428  bool has_prototype = IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode);
4429  int header_size = has_prototype ? JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype
4430  : JSFunction::kSizeWithoutPrototype;
4431  int inobject_properties_count = 0;
4432  // length and prototype accessors or just length accessor.
4433  int descriptors_count = IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode) ? 2 : 1;
4434  if (IsFunctionModeWithName(function_mode)) {
4435  ++inobject_properties_count; // name property.
4436  } else {
4437  ++descriptors_count; // name accessor.
4438  }
4439  descriptors_count += inobject_properties_count;
4440 
4441  DirectHandle<Map> map = NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4442  JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, header_size + inobject_properties_count * kTaggedSize,
4443  TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, inobject_properties_count);
4444  {
4445  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4446  Tagged<Map> raw_map = *map;
4447  raw_map->set_has_prototype_slot(has_prototype);
4448  raw_map->set_is_constructor(has_prototype);
4449  raw_map->set_is_callable(true);
4450  // Temporarily set constructor to empty function to calm down map verifier.
4451  raw_map->SetConstructor(*empty_function);
4452  }
4453  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, empty_function);
4454 
4455  //
4456  // Setup descriptors array.
4457  //
4458  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, descriptors_count);
4459 
4460  PropertyAttributes rw_attribs =
4461  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE);
4462  PropertyAttributes ro_attribs =
4463  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY);
4464  PropertyAttributes roc_attribs =
4465  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY);
4466 
4467  int field_index = 0;
4468  static_assert(JSFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex == 0);
4469  { // Add length accessor.
4470  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4471  length_string(), function_length_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4472  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4473  }
4474 
4475  static_assert(JSFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex == 1);
4476  if (IsFunctionModeWithName(function_mode)) {
4477  // Add name field.
4478  DirectHandle<Name> name = isolate()->factory()->name_string();
4479  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), name, field_index++,
4480  roc_attribs, Representation::Tagged());
4481  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4482 
4483  } else {
4484  // Add name accessor.
4485  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4486  name_string(), function_name_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4487  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4488  }
4489 
4490  if (IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode)) {
4491  // Add prototype accessor.
4492  PropertyAttributes attribs =
4493  IsFunctionModeWithWritablePrototype(function_mode) ? rw_attribs
4494  : ro_attribs;
4495  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4496  prototype_string(), function_prototype_accessor(), attribs);
4497  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4498  }
4499  DCHECK_EQ(inobject_properties_count, field_index);
4500  DCHECK_EQ(
4501  0, map->instance_descriptors(isolate())->number_of_slack_descriptors());
4502  LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(*map));
4503  return map;
4504 }

4506 DirectHandle<Map> Factory::CreateClassFunctionMap(
4507  DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function) {
4508  DirectHandle<Map> map = NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4509  JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE, JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype);
4510  {
4511  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4512  Tagged<Map> raw_map = *map;
4513  raw_map->set_has_prototype_slot(true);
4514  raw_map->set_is_constructor(true);
4515  raw_map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
4516  raw_map->set_is_callable(true);
4517  // Temporarily set constructor to empty function to calm down map verifier.
4518  raw_map->SetConstructor(*empty_function);
4519  }
4520  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, empty_function);
4521 
4522  //
4523  // Setup descriptors array.
4524  //
4525  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 2);
4526 
4527  PropertyAttributes ro_attribs =
4528  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY);
4529  PropertyAttributes roc_attribs =
4530  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY);
4531 
4532  static_assert(JSFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex == 0);
4533  { // Add length accessor.
4534  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4535  length_string(), function_length_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4536  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4537  }
4538 
4539  {
4540  // Add prototype accessor.
4541  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4542  prototype_string(), function_prototype_accessor(), ro_attribs);
4543  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4544  }
4545  LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(*map));
4546  return map;
4547 }

4591 DirectHandle<JSSharedStruct> Factory::NewJSSharedStruct(
4592  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor,
4593  MaybeDirectHandle<NumberDictionary> maybe_elements_template) {
4594  SharedObjectSafePublishGuard publish_guard;
4595 
4596  DirectHandle<Map> instance_map(constructor->initial_map(), isolate());
4597  DirectHandle<PropertyArray> property_array;
4598  const int num_oob_fields =
4599  instance_map->NumberOfFields(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous) -
4600  instance_map->GetInObjectProperties();
4601  if (num_oob_fields > 0) {
4602  property_array =
4603  NewPropertyArray(num_oob_fields, AllocationType::kSharedOld);
4604  }
4605 
4606  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> elements_dictionary;
4607  bool has_elements_dictionary;
4608  if ((has_elements_dictionary =
4609  maybe_elements_template.ToHandle(&elements_dictionary))) {
4610  elements_dictionary = NumberDictionary::ShallowCopy(
4611  isolate(), elements_dictionary, AllocationType::kSharedOld);
4612  }
4613 
4614  DirectHandle<JSSharedStruct> instance = Cast<JSSharedStruct>(
4615  NewJSObject(constructor, AllocationType::kSharedOld));
4616 
4617  // The struct object has not been fully initialized yet. Disallow allocation
4618  // from this point on.
4619  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4620  if (!property_array.is_null()) instance->SetProperties(*property_array);
4621  if (has_elements_dictionary) instance->set_elements(*elements_dictionary);
4622 
4623  return instance;
4624 }

4626 DirectHandle<JSSharedArray> Factory::NewJSSharedArray(
4627  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor, int length) {
4628  SharedObjectSafePublishGuard publish_guard;
4629  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> storage =
4630  NewFixedArray(length, AllocationType::kSharedOld);
4631  auto instance =
4632  Cast<JSSharedArray>(NewJSObject(constructor, AllocationType::kSharedOld));
4633  instance->set_elements(*storage);
4634  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(
4635  constructor->initial_map(),
4636  InternalIndex(JSSharedArray::kLengthFieldIndex));
4637  instance->FastPropertyAtPut(index, Smi::FromInt(length), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4638  return instance;
4639 }

4681 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> Factory::NewFunctionTemplateInfo(
4682  int length, bool do_not_cache) {
4683  const int size = FunctionTemplateInfo::SizeFor();
4684  Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> obj =
4685  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
4686  size, AllocationType::kOld,
4687  read_only_roots().function_template_info_map()));
4688  {
4689  // Disallow GC until all fields of obj have acceptable types.
4690  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4691  Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> raw = *obj;
4692  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
4693  InitializeTemplateWithProperties(raw, roots, !do_not_cache);
4694  raw->set_class_name(roots.undefined_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4695  raw->set_interface_name(roots.undefined_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4696  raw->set_signature(roots.undefined_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4697  raw->set_rare_data(roots.undefined_value(), kReleaseStore,
4698  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4699  raw->set_shared_function_info(roots.undefined_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4700  raw->set_cached_property_name(roots.the_hole_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4701 
4702  raw->set_flag(0, kRelaxedStore);
4703  raw->set_undetectable(false);
4704  raw->set_needs_access_check(false);
4705  raw->set_accept_any_receiver(true);
4706  raw->set_exception_context(
4707  static_cast<uint32_t>(ExceptionContext::kUnknown));
4708 
4709  raw->set_length(length);
4710  raw->SetInstanceType(0);
4711  raw->init_callback(isolate(), kNullAddress);
4712  raw->set_callback_data(roots.the_hole_value(), kReleaseStore,
4713  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4714  }
4715  return direct_handle(obj, isolate());
4716 }

4765 Factory::JSFunctionBuilder::JSFunctionBuilder(
4766  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi,
4767  DirectHandle<Context> context)
4768  : isolate_(isolate), sfi_(sfi), context_(context) {}
4769 
4770 Handle<JSFunction> Factory::JSFunctionBuilder::Build() {
4771  DirectHandle<Code> code(sfi_->GetCode(isolate_), isolate_);
4772  // Retain the code across the call to BuildRaw, because it allocates and can
4773  // trigger code to be flushed. Otherwise the SFI's compiled state and the
4774  // function's compiled state can diverge, and the call to PostInstantiation
4775  // below can fail to initialize the feedback vector.
4776  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(sfi_->is_compiled_scope(isolate_));
4777  Handle<JSFunction> result = BuildRaw(code);
4778 
4779  if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE) {
4780  JSFunction::EnsureFeedbackVector(isolate_, result, &is_compiled_scope);
4781  }
4782 
4783  Compiler::PostInstantiation(isolate_, result, &is_compiled_scope);
4784  return result;
4785 }
4786 
4787 Handle<JSFunction> Factory::JSFunctionBuilder::BuildRaw(
4788  DirectHandle<Code> code) {
4789  Isolate* isolate = isolate_;
4790  Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
4791 
4792  DirectHandle<Map> map;
4793  if (!maybe_map_.ToHandle(&map)) {
4794  // No specific map requested, use the default.
4795  map = direct_handle(Cast<Map>(context_->native_context()->GetNoCell(
4796  sfi_->function_map_index())),
4797  isolate_);
4798  }
4799  DCHECK(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(*map));
4800 
4801  Handle<JSFunction> function_handle;
4802  bool many_closures_cell = false;
4803  {
4804  // Allocation.
4805  Tagged<JSFunction> function =
4806  Cast<JSFunction>(factory->New(map, allocation_type_));
4807 
4808  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4809 
4810  // Transition the feedback cell after allocating the JSFunction. This is so
4811  // that the leap-tiering-relevant one-to-many feedback cell mutation below
4812  // happens atomically with the closure count increase here, without the
4813  // object verifier potentially observing a many-closures cell with context
4814  // specialised code.
4815  DirectHandle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell;
4816  FeedbackCell::ClosureCountTransition cell_transition;
4817  if (maybe_feedback_cell_.ToHandle(&feedback_cell)) {
4818  // Track the newly-created closure.
4819  cell_transition = feedback_cell->IncrementClosureCount(isolate_);
4820  } else {
4821  // Fall back to the many_closures_cell.
4822  feedback_cell = isolate_->factory()->many_closures_cell();
4823  cell_transition = FeedbackCell::kMany;
4824  many_closures_cell = true;
4825  }
4826 
4827  WriteBarrierMode mode = allocation_type_ == AllocationType::kYoung
4828  ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER
4829  : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
4830  // Header initialization.
4831  function->initialize_properties(isolate);
4832  function->initialize_elements();
4833  function->set_shared(*sfi_, mode);
4834  function->set_context(*context_, kReleaseStore, mode);
4835  function->set_raw_feedback_cell(*feedback_cell, mode);
4836 
4837 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4838  if (!many_closures_cell) {
4839  // TODO(olivf, 42204201): Here we are explicitly not updating (only
4840  // potentially initializing) the code. Worst case the dispatch handle
4841  // still contains bytecode or CompileLazy and we'll tier on the next call.
4842  // Otoh, if we would UpdateCode we would risk tiering down already
4843  // existing closures with optimized code installed.
4844  DCHECK_NE(*feedback_cell, *isolate->factory()->many_closures_cell());
4845  DCHECK_NE(feedback_cell->dispatch_handle(), kNullJSDispatchHandle);
4846 
4847  JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle = feedback_cell->dispatch_handle();
4848  JSDispatchTable* jdt = IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table();
4849  Tagged<Code> old_code = jdt->GetCode(dispatch_handle);
4850 
4851  // A write barrier is needed when settings code, because the update can
4852  // race with marking which could leave the dispatch slot unmarked.
4853  // TODO(olivf): This should be fixed by using a more traditional WB
4854  // for dispatch handles (i.e. have a marking queue with dispatch handles
4855  // instead of marking through the handle).
4856  constexpr WriteBarrierMode mode_if_setting_code =
4857  WriteBarrierMode::UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
4858 
4859  // TODO(olivf): We should go through the cases where this is still
4860  // needed and maybe find some alternative to initialize it correctly
4861  // from the beginning.
4862  if (old_code->is_builtin()) {
4863  jdt->SetCodeNoWriteBarrier(dispatch_handle, *code);
4864  function->set_dispatch_handle(dispatch_handle, mode_if_setting_code);
4865  } else {
4866  // On a transition of a feedback cell from one closure to many, make
4867  // sure that the code on the feedback cell isn't native context
4868  // specialized, and if it was, eagerly re-optimize.
4869  if (cell_transition == FeedbackCell::kOneToMany &&
4870  old_code->is_context_specialized()) {
4871  jdt->SetCodeNoWriteBarrier(dispatch_handle, *code);
4872  function->set_dispatch_handle(dispatch_handle, mode_if_setting_code);
4873  DCHECK(old_code->kind() == CodeKind::MAGLEV ||
4874  old_code->kind() == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
4875  if (!old_code->marked_for_deoptimization()) {
4876  function->RequestOptimization(isolate, old_code->kind());
4877  }
4878  } else {
4879  function->set_dispatch_handle(dispatch_handle, mode);
4880  }
4881  }
4882  }
4883 #else
4884  USE(cell_transition, many_closures_cell);
4885  function->UpdateCode(isolate, *code, mode);
4886 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4887 
4888  if (function->has_prototype_slot()) {
4889  function->set_prototype_or_initial_map(
4890  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).the_hole_value(), kReleaseStore,
4891  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4892  }
4893 
4894  // Potentially body initialization.
4895  factory->InitializeJSObjectBody(
4896  function, *map, JSFunction::GetHeaderSize(map->has_prototype_slot()));
4897 
4898  function_handle = handle(function, isolate_);
4899  }
4900 
4901 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4902  // If the FeedbackCell doesn't have a dispatch handle, we need to allocate a
4903  // dispatch entry now. This should only be the case for functions using the
4904  // generic many_closures_cell (for example builtin functions), and only for
4905  // functions using certain kinds of code.
4906  if (many_closures_cell) {
4907  // We currently only expect to see these kinds of Code here. For BASELINE
4908  // code, we will allocate a FeedbackCell after building the JSFunction. See
4909  // JSFunctionBuilder::Build.
4910  DCHECK(code->kind() == CodeKind::BUILTIN ||
4911  code->kind() == CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION ||
4912  code->kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE);
4913  // TODO(saelo): in the future, we probably want to use
4914  // code->parameter_count() here instead, but not all Code objects know
4915  // their parameter count yet.
4916  function_handle->clear_dispatch_handle();
4917  HeapObject::AllocateAndInstallJSDispatchHandle(
4918  function_handle, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset, isolate,
4919  sfi_->internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver(), code);
4920  } else {
4921  DCHECK_NE(function_handle->dispatch_handle(), kNullJSDispatchHandle);
4922  }
4923 #endif
4924 
4925  return function_handle;
4926 }
4927 
4928 } // namespace internal
4929 } // namespace v8
